title: batter for fish
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth. Good mix for sturgeon, prawns, etc.
Dip fish and deep fry on medium-high until golden brown.

title: english trifle
directions: Follow directions on cake box.
Bake 2 layers of cake.
Let cool and split layers.
Put layer of cake in bowl, put a layer of strawberries, pudding, Cool Whip and almonds.
Repeat until all ingredients are gone.
Top with almonds and let set for 8 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine butter, 2 tablespoons sugar and flour and blend until dough forms.
Press into 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until slightly browned.
Cool.
Fill pie shell with strawberries, slicing some so that pie is nicely filled.

title: lemon blueberry poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Rinse blueberries in cold water and drain.
Combine muffin mix and poppy seed in medium bowl.
Break up any lumps.
Add egg and water. Stir until moistened, about 50 strokes.
Fold in blueberries and lemon peel.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with contents of topping packet from mix.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen loaf.
Invert on rack.
Cool completely.

title: scottish shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and Crisco well.
Add brown sugar first a little at a time.
Then the white sugar, then gradually the flour.
I pat into two cookie sheets or a jelly roll pan.
Should be quite thin. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb pineapple pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, pineapple, tapioca, sugar, salt and water; let stand about 15 minutes.
Fill pastry with fruit mixture.
Combine brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter to make topping; sprinkle over fruit.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or until syrup boils with heavy bubbles that do not burst.
This recipe makes 1 pie.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix cubed chicken, celery and almonds together, then add salt, onion, lemon juice (or orange juice) and mayonnaise.
Mix.
Put in casserole and top with Cheddar cheese and crushed potato chips. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Do not overbake.

title: best dressing for salads
directions: Put all ingredients in the bottle and shake well. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: miso soup with bean sprouts
directions: Combine the miso and water in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes, or until boiling.

title: cheese spinach squares
directions: Beat eggs; add flour, baking powder and dressing mix.
Stir in melted butter.
Add shredded cheese and spinach.
Mixture will be thick; blend well.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: easy brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg and water.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to batter.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread; roll out into a rectangle.
Spread out as much as possible.
Cover with pepperoni and cheese.
Roll as you would a jelly roll, lengthwise.
Pinch and seal edges and shape. Place, seam side down.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover pan with foil for easy clean up.

title: easy rhubarb cake
directions: In a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan, spread the rhubarb on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle sugar, jello, tapioca and marshmallows over rhubarb.
Make the cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over mixture in pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples in buttered baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup white sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients with margarine until crumbly; pour over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender and top is brown (40 minutes).

title: egg in a nest
directions: Remove crust from bread.
With inverted glass, cut circle from center of bread.
Melt butter in frying pan; place bread in pan. Break egg in hole and cook.
Turn over, if desired, to cook further.

title: california broccoli salad
directions: Mix early so sugar can dissolve.
Use broccoli flowerets only. Mix finely chopped onion, crumbled crisp bacon, sunflower seeds and grapes together.
Just before serving, toss with dressing. Serves 6 to 8.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Add buttermilk and soda.
Sift together baking powder and 3 1/2 cups of flour.
Add to other ingredients.
Use remaining flour to handle.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: sweetbread pudding
directions: Melt butter; add milk and sugar.
Cool.
Add the beaten eggs to the butter
mixture; mix.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, break the sweetbread	into
pieces
and
distribute
evenly.	Spread apple pie
filling
over	the sweetbread.
Pour the butter-egg mixture evenly over
the top.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cornmeal in large bowl.
Toss lightly with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat with mixer until smooth and thoroughly blended.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: potato soup
directions: In deep saucepan, cook onion and mushrooms in hot oil until tender and lightly browned.
Add potatoes, beef and chicken broth; bring to a boil, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 35 to 45 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix together and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry pie (1)
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, strawberry jello and water.	Cook on stove until thickened.
Cool down and add 4 c. of cut up strawberries.
Put into graham cracker crust with 1/4 to 1/2 of cream cheese that has been mixed with one tsp. of sugar. Spread on graham crust or regular baked pie crust.
Pour cooled filling into crust.
When pie has cooled, add Cool Whip and garnish with a few cut up pieces of sliced strawberries.

title: ham barbecues
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients for 30 minutes.
Add ham and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: baby food cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into 12 x 18-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot savory pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Toss with steak strips to coat.
Add to crock-pot with onion, garlic and 1/2 the pepper strips; stir.
Combine tomatoes with beef base, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
One hour before serving, turn to high and stir in the rest of the bell peppers.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Wash rhubarb and cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Combine flour and sugar.
Mix with eggs. Combine with rhubarb.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 40 minutes at 350°.
Very easy to make and delicious!

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt margarine and pour over chicken.
Sift baking powder, salt and flour.
Blend well and spread over chicken.
In saucepan, mix soup and broth and bring to a boil.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: tony sobieski's tomato soup
directions: Place 3 tablespoons of butter and the olive oil in a soup kettle; heat over a low flame.
Peel and dice the onions.
Saute the onions in the soup kettle, sprinkling them with thyme, basil, salt and pepper, stirring occasionally.
Cut and mash the tomatoes in a bowl.
When the onions are yellowed and soft, stir in the tomatoes and tomato paste; simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour 1/4 cup of chicken stock into a small bowl; stir in the flour.
Add this liquid to the tomatoes and onions, mixing well.
Add the remainder of the chicken stock to the tomatoes, stirring well.
Cover the soup kettle; simmer the soup over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl; set aside. Combine egg, milk and oil; mix well.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Pour in liquid ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield: 12 muffins.

title: better way rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix well.
Add sugar, salt, 1/2 the flour, shortening and eggs; beat well.
Add rest of flour. Beat well.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Form dough into rolls and place on greased sheet.
Let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 400°.
Makes approximately 15.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together.
You may add marshmallows or any of your favorite ingredients.

title: arizona wagonwheel
directions: Melt 2 Tbsp. butter in large pan.
Add hotdogs and fry till slightly browned.
Add onion and saut until soft.
Add catsup (I add about 1/2 cup water to make it more moist).
Add spices and simmer about 20 - 30 minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: potato soup with cheese
directions: Boil the potatoes, onion, celery, salt and pepper until potatoes are soft.	Add
butter
and
simmer
slowly
1/2 to 1 hour.
Add cheese. Stir until cheese is melted and serve.

title: nana's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray. Beat butter in large bowl with an electric mixer set at medium speed until light and fluffy. Add granulated sugar and brown sugar; beat well. Add egg, egg whites and vanilla; beat until well blended. Add mashed banana and beat on high 30 seconds.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder in medium bowl. Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with cream, ending with flour mixture. Add walnuts to batter; mix well.
Pour batter evenly into prepared loaf pan. Bake until browned and toothpick inserted near center comes out clean, about 1 hour 15 minutes.
Cool bread in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove bread from pan; cool completely on wire rack. Slice and serve with butter and jam.

title: almond triangles
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Beat 1/2 pound butter, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and almond extract.
Beat in egg and then flour. Press dough into pan and push up sides.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Prick dough with fork and bake 10 minutes.
In pan combine brown sugar, honey and 1/2 pound butter and remaining sugar and cook over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Bring mixture to a boil without stirring and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in heavy cream and almonds.
Spread over crust and bake 15 minutes or until bubbling at 375°.
Cool and cut into triangles.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Squeeze cucumbers to get liquid out.
Slice onions thin, mix together and add sour cream.
Better to mix ahead of your meal.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar together in a bowl and let sit until sugar is dissolved.
In another bowl, mix pineapple and marshmallows.
Add these 2 mixtures to the Dream Whip and freeze.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Fry the salt pork in a skillet until crisp, then remove from the skillet and chop.
Saute the okra in pan drippings, then add the onion and fry until tender, stirring constantly.
Push the vegetables to one side of skillet, then brown the flour.
Mix the onion and okra into the flour and add the tomatoes, oyster liquor and boiling water gradually, stirring constantly, until smooth. Add the seasonings and stir well, then simmer for 1 hour.
Add the salt pork, crabmeat and shrimp and simmer a few minutes.
Add the oysters and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in file just before serving.
Serve in soup bowls over rice.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix together by hand.
Add 1 cup blueberries.
Bake in a 2 1/2-quart dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mock chicken dinner
directions: Using rolling pin, crush chips into small pieces.
Put a 1/3 of these layered on bottom of greased 2 quart casserole.
(Can use oil from tuna to grease pan.)
Add 1/3 of tuna as a layer.
Mix milk and soup and pour 1/3 of this over layers.
Continue until all ingredients are gone, finishing with some chips on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Kids love this one.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle both sides of chops with salt. Place pork chops in ungreased shallow baking pan or dish.
Top each pork chop with onion slice, lemon slice, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon ketchup.
Cover and bake 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, spooning sauce onto pork chops occasionally until done.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: *Do not use self-rising flour with this recipe.

title: poppin fresh cookies
directions: Spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Combine flour and baking soda and set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Blend well with mixer.
Add by hand the remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheets and cool.

title: brunch dish
directions: Remove crust from the bread. Place 8 slices in bottom of greased casserole dish. Top with slices of ham, slices of cheese, then 8 slices of bread. Beat eggs, salt, mustard and milk. Pour over rest. Cover and refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours. Before baking, pour melted butter over top and sprinkle with potato chips that are crushed up. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 1 hour).
Makes 2 small or 1 large pie.

title: herb biscuits
directions: Melt oleo. Add seasoning and divide in 2 (9-inch) round pans. Cut biscuits in 4 pieces and place on top of butter mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Invert biscuits onto plate to serve.

title: key lime pie(the easy way)
directions: Combine condensed milk and lime juice thoroughly. Add 1/2 of the Cool Whip and fold in. Pour into prepared graham cracker crust. Spread other half of Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: avocado lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water.
In a large bowl, mix the hot sauce and mayonnaise.
Spoon Jell-O into mixed sauce and mayonnaise to prevent mayonnaise from lumping.
Add chopped onion. Let set until it starts to jell.
Add finely chopped celery and avocados that have been cut into medium sized chunks.
Let set until firm.
May sprinkle with paprika when serving on lettuce cups.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in the crockpot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 6 hours or high for 3 hours.

title: lou's spinach
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased uncovered dish. Top with Pepperidge Farm herb dressing. Dot with butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and chill about 1 hour. Serve.

title: coconut crumb cherry pie
directions: Bake a pie shell at 450° for 5 minutes.
Bring pie filling just to a boil; pour into pie shell.
Combine flour, sugar and butter.
Then add coconut to mixture.
Sprinkle over pie filling.

title: hungarian cabbage and noodles
directions: Mix all the above ingredients in a bowl, except the cabbage. Add more flour, if necessary, to make this biscuit dough consistency. Drop in boiling, salted water by the teaspoonfuls to cook. When done they will rise to the top. Remove and rinse with hot water. Do not use cold water. Drain and set aside.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: Break up angel food cake into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans on cake.
Melt chocolate chips and Hershey bars in 3 tablespoons hot water.
Cool.
Beat 4 egg yolks and add to chocolate mixture.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff and fold into chocolate mixture.
Whip the 1/2 pint of whipping cream.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour over the cake and pecans in the pan. Refrigerate for 24 hours; overnight works well.
Great special day dessert.

title: orange sponge cake(delours sunshine cake)
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon yellow colored. Add orange juice and beat until very thick. Gradually beat in 1 c of the sugar and the salt. Carefully fold in the flour and orange peel. Beat the egg whites until foamy, add the cream of tartar and beat until soft peaks form. Gradually add the remaining 1/2 c. sugar beating until stiff peaks form. Thoroughly fold the whites into the yolk and flour mixture. Pour into an ungreased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: orange gelatin salad
directions: Mix Jell-Os and boiling water until Jell-O dissolved.
In small amounts, add cream cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Add pineapple (juice and all) and oranges which have been cut in 2 pieces if large.
Add a small amount of orange juice.
Add 7-Up.
Pour into an 11 x 7 (or about this size) pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Chill until firm.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Mixture will be stiff.
Put batter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour this mixture over dough in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling into a square casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and skim milk.
Sprinkle Butter Buds on top of fruit.
Pour batter mix on top of the fruit.
Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar mixture on top of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with nonfat frozen yogurt or Dream Whip.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cold mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook mixed vegetables, drain and cool.
Marinate 12 hours with French dressing.

title: henry's coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour over grated cabbage and carrots.

title: diane's chicken spaghetti
directions: Microwave a whole chicken 9 to 10 minutes per pound (or cook in water).
Saute onions and green peppers in olive oil.
Prepare a package of spaghetti sauce according to package directions but use chicken broth from cooked chicken instead of water.
Add mushrooms and cook for a while.
Add boned, diced chicken.
Cook spaghetti and add to sauce.
When using for leftovers, add Ragu.

title: quick, easy punch
directions: Mix fruit punch and ginger ale.
Place sherbet on top, enough for taste.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the hot water.
Add 1 cup juice from apricots and crushed pineapple.
Crush apricots and add with the crushed pineapple to Jell-O.
Let set.

title: mom's rice balls
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Drain if necessary.
Mix all remaining ingredients together and then add warm rice.
(Use a large bowl, this makes a lot.)
After rice mixture is well blended, form into balls about the size of a tennis ball.
Roll in bread crumbs and fry in hot (350°) oil, a few at a time until golden brown.
Makes about 21 rice balls.

title: a man's casserole
directions: Fry onions until tender.
Add beef and seasonings to taste. Cook until red in meat is gone.
Layer in greased casserole dish, 1/3 of cooked noodles, 1/2 of meat mixture, 1/2 of soup and milk mixture, 1/3 of noodles, 1/2 of meat mixture, 1/2 of soup mixture and rest of noodles.
Top with cheese and beaten eggs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio - coconut surprise
directions: Combine sour cream and pudding mix.
Add coconut and pineapple and stir until blended.
Spoon into 8 x 4 or 9 x 5 inch loaf pan and freeze until firm at least 3 hours.
Dip pan in warm water and unmold onto serving plate.
Makes 3 cups or 6 servings. Note:
Instead of freezing, fruit salad may be prepared and served immediately or chilled.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a warm skillet, combine the rhubarb, sugar, flour, cinnamon, jello and margarine. Stir until melted, then set aside to cool.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Dissolve strawberry and lime
Jello (each one in the usual way) and pour into 2 different cookie sheets.
Jell, then cut in small squares.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in hot pineapple juice and sugar.
Let jell slightly.
Whip the large package of Dream Whip, then fold in lemon mixture.
Then add Jell-O cubes. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with graham cracker crust.
Let stand in refrigerator.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix melted margarine with stuffing mix.
Place 1/2 of this mixture in oblong casserole dish.
Put chicken on top of stuffing mix.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over chicken.
Add sage to remaining stuffing mix.
Place on top and pour chicken broth over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: conaway's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir all ingredients together except ketchup. Shape into two small loaves.
Put in baking pan and add 1 cup water.
Cover with tinfoil and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes. Add ketchup to top of the loaves and continue baking, uncovered, during the last 15 minutes.

title: polka dots
directions: Combine oats, salt, milk and vanilla.
Blend in peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Press mixture into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: no bake cheesecake with cherry on top
directions: Follow package directions for cheese cake.
Chill.
When cold, add cherry to top and enjoy.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring contents to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-high and cook 5 minutes or until the cranberry skins begin to pop.
Cool and serve with meats.

title: banana chiffon cake
directions: Let yolks and whites warm to room temperature.
Start heating oven to 325°.

title: cherry cheese dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt butter.
Mix brown sugar and then slowly add flour and nuts to the butter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: mavis' pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix soda in sour cream. Add flour alternately with sour cream and soda mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Next beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold in other mixture.
Add flavorings.
Put mixture into Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam and floured.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before turning out.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to batter alternately with the sour cream.
Fold in flavoring.
Put in a large tube pan or Bundt pan that has been well greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for one and one half hours.

title: clove sauce for baked ham(per serving)
directions: Melt margarine on a low burner.
Add mustard, sugar and cloves.
Stir at low heat until it "clears".

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place cut up chicken in to marinate (overnight is good).

title: sausage rotel dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Add softened cream cheese and rotel and mix well.
Great with the big corn chips.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Heat in microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: waldorf imperial salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a large mixing bowl and toss with the mayonnaise.
Garnish with cherries and chill before serving. Makes 9 cups.

title: grandpa's stewed gizzards
directions: All all ingredients, except rice, in a large stewing pot. Over medium flame, stew until gizzards are tender.
Once tender, serve over rice.

title: zucchini salad(bulgaria)
directions: Clean and wash the zucchini, then cut into medium sized pieces. Boil in salt water. When ready, drain well and place in salad bowl, pour oil, vinegar, garlic and 2-3 tablespoons of the boiling liquid, mix. Garnish with chopped parsley and dill.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix with water until desired consistency.
Spoon in small amounts into hot oil.
Fry until golden.

title: rancherette pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 200.
Break up pretzels and mix next four ingredients together and pour over pretzels, mix well and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 200 for 20 minutes.
Store in air tight container.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn onto plate and immediately place Bundt pan back over cake or put in Tupperware and place top over cake to make it sweat.
Best to make a couple days ahead.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Cook lean roast in oven until well done.
Allow to cool and slice into thin slices.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients and store in container. Use 1 1/2 to 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water for a tasty drink.

title: oven omelet
directions: Beat together the eggs, milk and salt and pour over bread. Add sausage and cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese bread souffle
directions: Crumble bread finely into large mixing bowl.
Heat milk until almost simmering.
Remove from heat and blend small amount into egg yolks.
Gradually add egg mixture to remaining milk, salt and spice.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and pimento; stir until cheese melts. Blend into crumbs.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Thoroughly fold into bread mixture.
Put into a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes until an inserted knife comes out clean.
Serve immediately . . . won't wait.

title: calico beans
directions: All other beans should be drained.

title: porter beans-barbecue
directions: Soak beans overnight or parboil with a teaspoon of soda; rinse.
Mix together and cook slowly for several hours.

title: onion casserole
directions: Peel and wash onions.
Cut into chunks.
Boil until tender; drain.
Melt margarine in onions and saute for 3 minutes.
Set aside.
Mix milk and eggs; beat well.
Add onions, 1 cup grated cheese and 25 crumbled crackers.

title: tabouli
directions: Combine bulgur, water and salt in a bowl.
Cover; let stand 15 to 20 minutes, until bulgur is chewable.
Add lemon juice, garlic, oil and mint.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: ham sandwiches
directions: Cream margarine, onion, poppy seed and mustard.
Spread on both sides of buns.
Place ham and cheese on bun.
Put together and spread mustard mixture on top of bun.
Wrap in foil and bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.
These sandwiches may be made ahead and frozen.
These may also be used as an appetizer when made on tiny Parker House rolls.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix for two minutes.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix all ingredients except sausage.
Add sausage last.
Then add 3 cups of water.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Either grate or blend corned beef. Combine with all ingredients and mix well. Serve with crackers or celery sticks.

title: one day sweet pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt with hands.
Let stand 2 hours. Drain well and squeeze out juice.

title: onion soup
directions: In 4 to 6-quart Dutch oven or kettle, heat butter and oil until hot.
Add onions and sugar.
Cook over medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently, until onions are lightly browned and bottom of pan is lightly glazed.
Scrape glaze from bottom of pan and blend in with onions.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute.
Stir in beef bouillon, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir in Burgundy and Madeira.
Taste for seasoning.
Pour into tureen or ladle into soup bowls over rounds of bread.
Pass grated cheese separately.
Makes 2 2/3 quarts (8 to 10 servings).

title: hot and spicy szechwan
directions: Combine sugar, soy sauce and water.
Mix.
Heat oil.
Stir-fry meat in skillet.
Stir-fry with meat all vegetables except bamboo shoots and mushrooms.
Stir-fry remaining vegetables.
Add seasoning mixture. Stir-fry for 1 minute.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla. Sift and measure flour.
Add gradually to butter mixture.
Mix in nuts.
Roll dough into balls and place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While warm, coat with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pam spray 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.

title: hamburg surprise
directions: Mix all together, except
soup, cheese slices and Tater Tots. Pat in bottom of an 8 or 9-inch baking dish (use 13 x 9-inch and double recipe for a larger group).
Cover with the soup.
Top with the Tater Tots.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma lillie's russian cabbage soup
directions: Combine tomatoes and water in pot and bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to blend.
Simmer with lid ajar until meat is tender (2 to 2 1/2 hours).

title: chicken isabelle
directions: Rinse corned beef with water and place on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wrap each chicken breast with a piece of bacon and place on top of corned beef.
Mix soup, milk, sour cream and wine together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 300°, uncovered 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: harvest holiday ham with cider glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Trim fat from the ham. Cut it up in slices. Place on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Insert a meat thermometer. Roast, uncovered, about 1 1/2 to 2 1/4 hours or until thermometer registers 140°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Add apples and nuts; blend in.
Bake at 350°.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: Line three greased 9 inch round baking pans with waxed paper and grease the paper, set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites on high speed until stiff peaks form; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks and sugar until thick and lemon-colored.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Combine the cracker crumbs, nuts and baking powder; fold into egg yolk mixture. Gradually fold in egg whites.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 325° for 20-25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.

title: hamburger bundles
directions: Blend soup and milk in medium sized mixing bowl.
In a large bowl, combine beef, catsup and worcestershire sauce.
Divide beef mixture and shape into 4 patties.
Place 1/4 c. stuffing in center of each patty and draw sides of patty up to make a bowl.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Cover with soup mixture.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecos pasta salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine pasta, green onions, tomato, chilies, olives, corn, cilantro, lime juice and picante sauce. Stir to blend well.
Add enough mayo to coat salad ingredients well.
Refrigerate to let flavors blend before serving.

title: rotel chili
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Add meat and rice to the other ingredients. Heat on stove top or slowly in crock-pot.
Serve hot with cheese sprinkled on top of individual servings.

title: punch bowl cake - from texas
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix from box.
In a punch bowl, crumble 1/3 cake in bottom.
Put cherry pie filling on top of cake; add crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle vanilla instant pudding and nuts and top with Cool Whip.
Repeat in layers.

title: moist never fail chocolate cake
directions: Put ingredients in a bowl.
Do not mix until all ingredients are together.
Mix well and bake in loaf pan in a moderate 350° oven.

title: chicken a la queen
directions: Prepare a marinade of wine, corn syrup and cooking oil. Marinate 4 to 6 chicken breasts for at least 1 hour.
Prepare the dressing while chicken is marinating:

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix fat, sugar and eggs; mix in baking soda, salt and flour. Mix in rolled oats and raisins.
Drop dough by spoonfuls on baking pan.
Leave room for cookies to spread.
Bake at 375° (moderate oven) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: sweet-sour green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan. Add beans and liquid. Boil until almost dry. Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: great green beans
directions: Take beans out of can and drain.
Then drain potatoes and mix both in pan.
Take onion and put in mixture; pour liquid ingredients in over beans; salt and pepper to taste.
Boil all of this for about 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix altogether and add enough water to make 2 gallons.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on the box.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.

title: low calorie muffins
directions: Add bran to honey and milk.
Soak 15 minutes.
Beat egg; add to mixture.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Put 3 cups of flour with other ingredients; mix and stir.
Put rest of flour in and knead until smooth; let rise.
Butter pan and break dough into rolls.
Let rise again.
Cook until brown at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs and stir in milk.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder and stir into egg mixture.
Beat in oil and corn. Drop by spoonfuls into hot deep oil and fry at 375° until brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain off grease.
Add juice, seasoning and beans.
Heat to boiling and then simmer for 1/2 hour. (The longer it sits, the better it tastes.)

title: forcemeat balls
directions: Shred the ham or bacon; chop the suet, lemon peel and herbs, taking care that all be finely minced.
Season with salt, cayenne pepper and mace and blend all thoroughly together with the bread crumbs before wetting.
Now beat and strain the eggs; work these up with other ingredients, and the forcemeat will be ready.

title: mystery pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for brown sugar and nuts and pour in greased 9 x 9 inch pan.
Top with the sugar and nuts. Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.
Serve warm with a dollop of Cool Whip.
Serves 6.

title: mashed yam casserole
directions: Pierce yams all over with fork. Bake in microwave until cooked. Cut in half. Scoop pulp into a bowl. Add Marshmallow Creme, butter and syrup. Beat with mixer until smooth. Beat in eggs until blended. Season with salt and pepper (optional). This can be done one day ahead, covered and chilled.

title: one bowl applesauce cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter.
Add molasses, egg and applesauce.
Beat well.
Stir in raisins.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch square pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn out on cake rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or glaze.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green peppers.
Drain meat; cook noodles as directed on package.
Shred cabbage (not too thin).
Saute cabbage in butter until tender.
Fold in beef mixture, noodles and sour cream with cabbage.
Simmer on low heat for about 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well and bake in greased pan at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies. Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Then mix pudding with milk and then stir in Cool Whip.
Mix	all
of this together, but not the Oreos. Layer pudding
mixture,
then
Oreos, ending with Oreos in an 8-inch diameter plastic pot.
Serve with dirt scoop.

title: diane rehm's sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Chop pecans and mix with cinnamon and sugar in separate small bowl.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Spoon 1/3 batter into pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 pecan mixture. Spoon remaining batter into pan.
Sprinkle with rest of pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: scallops with brussels sprouts
directions: Boil Brussels sprouts in water and salt for 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: beef burgers hawaiian
directions: Mix garlic, salad oil, soy sauce, catsup, vinegar and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mix the meat, salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper thoroughly.
Shape into 6 patties.
Press 5 or 6 pineapple tidbits into each.
Place patties in glass dish; pour oil mixture over patties.
Cover; refrigerate 30 minutes, turning occasionally. Remove patties from marinade.
Wrap bacon slice around each patty; secure with wooden picks.
Broil 5 inches from heat for 12 to 15 minutes, turning once, or cook on hibachi over hot coals for 8 to 10 minutes on each side.
Serves 6.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix soups together; add water and heat.
Remove from stove. Mix in 1 1/4 cups long grained rice.
Pour into casserole dish. Add chicken breasts to casserole with a little salt and pepper, if desired.
Can also add several small dots of butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir several times, making sure chicken is covered.
Can add a little more water, if needed. Serves 8 to 12.

title: australian strawberry pie
directions: Mix together egg yolks, butter and sugar.
Add 1 tablespoon gelatin, softened in 1/4 cup cold water.
Heat on low to dissolve. Beat whipping cream and vanilla.
Add to egg mixture (fold in). Pour mixture into pie shell.
Top with strawberries and partially set jello.
Refrigerate to set.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add oil gradually; add flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and grated carrots.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch or two 8-inch round pans or even a Bundt pan well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown chuck. Add chopped onion and chopped green pepper; cook until tender. Add tomatoes and juice, rice, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder. Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook for about 10 more minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Cook all together on medium-low for 15 minutes.
Serve on hot dogs.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: In mixer, combine cream cheese, marshmallow cream and vanilla/almond extract.
Mix on medium speed until smooth and creamy.
Pour into dip bowl and serve with chilled fruit.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: apple butter
directions: Fill a 5-quart crock-pot to the top with chopped peeled apples.
Add sugar,
cinnamon and salt and cook on high for 1 hour.
Turn to low and cook all day or all night.
Stir a few times.

title: 7 week muffins
directions: Combine water and bran flakes; cool.
Add shortening and eggs; beat well.
Add buttermilk.
In another bowl, sift flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Fold into wet mixture.
Add Bran Buds and nuts. Store in a covered container in refrigerator.
Use as you wish within 7 weeks.
You can add chocolate chips just before baking. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: honey oatmeal bars
directions: Cream shortening, honey and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to cream mixture.
Add granola or other mixture.
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool cut into bars.

title: goodies
directions: Cream the butter until soft.
Gradually add the granulated sugar and continue creaming until smooth.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat until light.

Add the vanilla and the milk alternately with the flour which has been sifted with the baking powder and the salt, mixing thoroughly after each addition. Spread the batter in a greased and floured shallow pan (9 x 14-inch), sprinkle with chopped nut meats, confectioners sugar and the cinnamon.
Bake in a moderate oven, 350°, for about 25 minutes.
Remove from the oven and cut in bars (2 x 3/4-inch). Allow the bars to cool in the pan.

title: curry chicken salad
directions: Toss together chicken, rice and celery in large bowl.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Serve on shredded lettuce and garnish with black olives.
Yields 6 servings.

title: homemade mac and cheese
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk.
Add mustard powder.
Slowly add cheese.
Stir on low until sauce is thick.
Pour into baking dish with the macaroni.
Add broken bread bits.
Cook in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together; roll in small balls.
Cook on ungreased pan or cookie sheet at 350° until done.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into cupcake pans with paper liners.
Freeze until firm.
Store in plastic bags.
Remove from freezer and place on a lettuce leaf about 5 to 10 minutes before ready to eat so they can thaw a bit.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line or grease 18 muffin cups.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, salt, allspice, cinnamon, baking soda and flour.
In separate bowl, whisk together the eggs, oil, pumpkin and milk.
Add to flour mixture along with nuts.
Stir just until ingredients are moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: eggplant napoli
directions: In a skillet saute chopped onion in oil.
Add tomato puree, water, salt, oregano and pepper.
Bring to a bol and simmer for 15 minutes.

In a greased baking dish alternate thin layers of sliced eggplant, tomato sauce and half of the grated cheese, starting with layer of eggplant and ending with layer of tomato sauce. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Minutes before serving, sprinkle remaining grated cheese on top and continue baking until cheese melts.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add 1 cup sugar, beating constantly, then add next 4 ingredients.
Scald milk and butter.
Add all at once to first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While hot, spread on mixture of remaining ingredients.
Put under broiler until evenly browned.
(For thicker frosting, this mixture may be doubled.)

title: cookies and cream ice cream
directions: Beat
eggs
until
thick.
Add
sugar and beat about 15 minutes until creamy.
Add the Eagle Brand milk, half and half and the
whipping
cream.
Fold in the crushed cookies or you may wait and
add
the cookies after the ice cream has set for better texture.
If
added
before
freezing, the cookies dissolve and make a chocolate looking ice cream (tastes the same, but doesn't look
as
good).
Pour
mix
into
the
ice cream freezer and finish
filling
the
container
with milk.
Make according to the
directions
on
freezer.
When set turn out into large container;
add cookies and let freeze for about 1 hour.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine, corn syrup and salt together well.
Gradually stir in powdered sugar.
Knead until smooth. Gradually add nuts.
Pack into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Press remainder into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, building up about 1/2 inch around sides.
Spoon cherry pie filling over crumb mixture to 1/2 inch of edge of pan.
Combine reserved crumb mixture and pecans; sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir.
Sift flour.
Add cocoa, salt and nuts; mix together.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Put marshmallow cream on top.
Place in oven another 4 to 6 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate 1/2 hour to blend flavors.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix and cook for 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: sweet stuff
directions: Combine all ingredients in order as they come in recipe.
Bake in square pan at 350°.

title: lydia's dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Drain and stir.
Serve chilled with corn chips.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Combine sauerkraut and onion; toss until well mixed.
Spread dressing on each slice of bread.
Top 8 slices of bread with corned beef, cheese and sauerkraut mixture.
Top with remaining bread.
Spread both sides of sandwiches with butter.
Grill slowly until cheese melts and bread browns.

title: moist raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins and water; cook for 10 minutes.
Add butter.
Let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add raisin mixture to flour mixture.
Pour into greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheryl's mushroom quiche
directions: Layer croutons, sausage, mushroom pieces, soup and cheese in this order in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together and pour over ingredients in casserole.
Cover and let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash strawberries and hull. Put one half of berries in saucepan and crush.
Mix sugar and cornstarch; add to crushed berries along with lemon juice.
Cook on medium heat until mixture thickens.
Cool. Cut remaining berries into halves and mix with the cooked mixture.
Add a few drops of red food coloring to the cooked mixture before adding the uncooked berries. Chill before serving. Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: baked herbed potatoes
directions: Cook cubed potatoes in small amount boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and add remaining ingredients (which have been mixed together) all except parsley.
Put in 2-quart casserole; cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix and pour remaining ingredients over crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until smooth.
Fold the next three ingredients together.
Add to pudding mixture.
Put thin layer of pudding mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer wafers, bananas and pudding mixture twice.
Sprinkle some crumbled wafers on top.
Store in refrigerator.
Best if made 8 to 10 hours before serving.

title: ohelo cream pie
directions: Cream
cream cheese, powdered sugar and
vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip; spread over cooled crust.
Chill.
Place cleaned berries, water, lemon juice and sugar in pot;
cook
and bring to a
rolling boil.
Continue 3 minutes.
Remove
from
heat. Add gelatine which has been dissolved in 1/2
cup water.
Cool completely;
pour over cream cheese.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in salt, flour and baking powder, a little at a time.
Chill several hours or overnight. Drop by spoonfuls in sugar and roll into ball.
Bake on slightly greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart, 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Makes 50 to 75 cookies.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add the cracker crumbs, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips or Heath chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour the Eagle Brand over top of all. Bake at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes. Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemonade
directions: In jar shake
together sugar, lemon peel and 1 1/2 cups very hot water
until
sugar
is
dissolved.
Add lemon juice. Refrigerate two hours.

title: watermelon man's salsa
directions: Ice down a melon.
Draw a pitcher of beer.
Cut and core red tomatoes.
Cut and dice Bermuda onions.
Split jalapeno peppers and core out seeds, dice.
Peel garlic cloves and dice.
Cut lime, remove seeds and squeeze juice.
Add salt.
Mash in stainless steel pot with potato masher.
Put in glass jar and refrigerate at least 2 days.
Can be eaten anytime.
Makes approximately 1 quart to be eaten with a woman.
Drink your beer.
Clean up mess.
Give your girl a watermelon bath!

title: mother's egg nog
directions: Whip the cream in small mixing bowl.
In another small mixing bowl, beat well the egg yolks plus 1 tablespoon sugar per yolk. To cook the yolks, slowly add nog or whiskey as yolks are beaten thoroughly.
(They should become lemon colored.)
In large mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff; add 1 tablespoon sugar per egg white.
Fold yolk mixture into whites and then fold in the whipped cream.
Serve in bowls with a spoon.
Sprinkle with nutmeg to taste.

title: bacon wrapped oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Place an oyster on each piece of bacon. Sprinkle with parsley and seasonings.
Wrap bacon around oyster and secure with a toothpick.
Place on broiler rack and broil about 4 inches from source of heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn carefully.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes longer or until bacon is crisp and oysters begin to curl at the edges.
Makes approximately 20 to 25 hors d'oeuvres.
Also good skewered on barbecue pit.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix
all ingredients and roll into 1-inch balls.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: shrimp with feta cheese
directions: In skillet, melt butter on low heat.
Add garlic and onion; saute until onion is soft (5 minutes).
Add tomatoes, basil, mustard and sugar.
Mix well and cook over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Add wine, parsley, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Mix over medium heat and add shrimp. Cook and stir frequently for 3 to 4 minutes until shrimp becomes pink (don't overcook).
Remove from skillet and transfer to open baking dish.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Sprinkle Feta cheese over top.
Bake for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve over angel hair pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable soup made with ground beef
directions: Fry ground meat; drain.
To meat, add other ingredients; cook for 1 hour or longer.

title: marshmallow crispies
directions: Grease large saucepan with vegetable spray.
Add marshmallows and melt over low heat.
Stir in cereal.
Mix well.
Spray spoon with vegetable spray and press mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Cut into 30 squares.

title: fluffy delight
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into bowl.
Drain pineapple tidbits. Add to cherries.
Slice the banana into other fruit.
Add the walnuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well and chill.
Preparation time 5 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt butter and mix all other ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and pepper until onion and pepper are almost tender.
Mix with soups and noodles in a casserole.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook in 300° oven for about 30 minutes.
Cut oven off.
Sprinkle entire top of casserole with grated cheese spread.
Let set in oven until cheese melts, but do not let noodles dry out.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in large saucepan.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
Cook over low heat for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened.
Mix small amount of hot mixture into beaten eggs.
Add eggs back to hot mixture; cook about 2 minutes longer.
Chill completely in refrigerator.
Add Carnation and vanilla.
Freeze in ice cream churn.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as recommended on box.
Rinse in colander and drain.
Add oil and vinegar and mix well.
Cover and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Add onion and pimentos.
Beat mayonnaise and heavy cream together and mix well with spaghetti before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix cream cheese and Cheddar cheese with a mixer.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts and mix well. Shape into a ball.
(This is easier to do if you chill cheese mixture first.)
Roll in nuts to cover.
Refrigerate.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter on low heat in a saucepan. Add Crispix cereal gradually and stir.
Pour powdered sugar in a paper sack and add cereal mixture.
Shake for a minute or so until well coated.
Ready to serve; will still be warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together cheese, onions, seasonings and 1 package of chopped chipped beef.
Form into a ball and roll in remaining chopped chipped beef.
Chill before serving with crackers.

title: barbecue beef in a bun
directions: Brown your hamburger and sausage together.
Drain well.
Add barbecue sauce enough to just moisten meat, set aside.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2 inch strips and place in a large plastic bag.
Combine egg, buttermilk and garlic powder and pour over chicken.
Seal and refrigerate 2-4 hours.
In another large reclosable bag, combine flour, bread crumbs, salt and baking powder.
Drain chicken and discard buttermilk mixture.
Place chicken in bag with flour mixture and seal.
Shake to coat.
Heat oil to 375 F and fry chicken 4-5 minutes or till golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Serves 6.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix together vinegar, sugar and Crisco oil.
Combine above mixture and remaining ingredients.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, Cool Whip and milk thoroughly in large mixing bowl.
Pour a very small amount of this mixture into bottom of a large rectangle Pyrex pan.
Start placing graham crackers in a single layer on bottom of pan.
Pour 1/2 of mixture on top of graham crackers and smooth.
Place another layer of graham crackers on top of mixture.
Pour remaining mixture on top of crackers. Place another layer of graham crackers on top.
Melt chocolate frosting (remove foil top) in microwave for about 45 seconds.
Stir and pour over last layer of graham crackers.
Smooth the icing nicely.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Combine and store in tight jar.
Use amount desired (about 2 teaspoons) per cup of hot water.
Delicious on a cold day!

title: my favorite chili
directions: Heat the oil.
Brown onion and remove from oil.
Set onion aside.
Brown beef until moisture disappears. Add beans and catsup; continue cooking, 15 to 18 minutes.
Add the hot water, chili powder, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and garlic. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: gingerbread boys and girls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add water and syrup and mix.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well and chill at least 1 hour.
Prepare a floured surface and roll out dough 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
If using as tree ornaments, make hole with toothpick or dried bean before cooking.
Before baking, place raisins for eyes, nose, mouth and buttons or decorate later with decorator icing after they are cooked and cooled.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: butter brickle bread
directions: Beat together.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or 3 medium-size pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Mix eggs, margarine and vanilla to desired thickness.

title: chocolate nut krispies
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar and syrup.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat.
Blend in peanut butter and margarine.
Stir in rice cereal. Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside.
In heavy saucepan, melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Spread melted chocolate over cereal mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Chill bars for 1 hour, or until topping is firm.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix, but do not beat.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: corny casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Put into a lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken rarebit
directions: Brown chicken in 1 tablespoon butter over high heat.
Arrange broccoli in baking dish.
Top with browned chicken.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add flour and cook for 1 minute over low heat.
Remove from heat; add beer.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover; bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serves 4.

title: easy lo-cal strawberry shortcake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add sliced frozen strawberries. Add 1/2 of a large carton Cool Whip.
Spray tube or Bundt pan with Pam.
Break cake into bite size pieces. Add a layer of cake in pan, then a layer of Jell-O mixture. Repeat until cake and Jell-O are gone.
Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Turn out of pan and top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage leaves in water to cover in saucepan until tender; drain and set aside.
Combine the next 7 ingredients in bowl with enough tomato sauce to moisten; mix well.
Roll meat mixture in cabbage leaves.
Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: granola
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake on cookie sheets at 275 degrees for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: ham and cauliflower casserole
directions: Mix in 9 x 13-inch pan cauliflower, ham, cheese and sour cream (consistency should be creamy).
Sprinkle in corn flakes, but leave some for top.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Cook enough sweet potatoes to make 1 quart of mashed potatoes. When tender, drain off water.
Add margarine, salt and brown sugar.
Beat with mixer until fluffy.
Add pecans and pineapple. Pour this mixture into baking dish; cover with marshmallows and bake at 350° until marshmallows are brown.
Serve hot.
Can be reheated.

title: kalaverdi
directions: Soak beans in water 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
In large pot, add olive oil, onions, sliced kielbasi and garlic.
Saute; do not brown.
Add chicken stock and navy beans; let cook 15 minutes. Add kale, crushed red pepper and sugar.
Let cook 20 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Stir well.
Let cook 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: apple peanut butter sandwiches
directions: Slice apple approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Dip each slice into lemon juice.
Put small amount of peanut butter between 2 slices of apple and enjoy!

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Soften gelatin in lemon juice, then dissolve over hot water.
Blend cream cheese with mayonnaise and salt.
Stir in gelatin.
Whip cream until stiff, adding sugar gradually during last stages of beating.
Fold in cheese mixture, nuts and fruit cocktail.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, chop lettuce.
Add chopped tomatoes. Add chopped pepper.
Add sliced radishes.
Mix thoroughly, then add the Ranch Style beans, Fritos and dressing.
Refrigerate for about 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mock frozen peach daiquiri
directions: Chill peaches in freezer until very cold.
Add to blender container with pink lemonade concentrate, lemon juice, egg white and crushed ice; puree until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Makes two (1 1/4 cup) servings.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, drain.
In a large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Add noodles and toss to coat.
Transfer to a 2 qt. baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Cover and bake 350 for 30 minutes. Uncover; bake 5 - 10 minutes longer or until heated through.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: pol's apple cake
directions: Blend eggs, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add flour a little at a time.
Blend well.
Batter will be stiff.
Fold in apples, coconut and nuts.
Pour into well greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool and turn out on plate and spread glaze over.

title: hot pork chops and beans
directions: In a large frying pan cook jalapenos and onion until soft and brown.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Fry pork chops until well done and crispy.
Over medium heat add beans, tomato sauce, jalapenos and onion, then add other ingredients.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Serve with warm corn tortillas.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Mix sour cream, coconut and sugar. Stir well.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Fill cake between layers with coconut mixture, saving 1 cup of mixture.
Mix saved cup with 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
"Ice" cake and refrigerate for 2 days.

title: quick homemade chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add garlic and ground beef.
Stir until beef loses its red color.
Add beans with liquid, onion and green pepper.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and chili powder. Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, until chili is of desired thickness, about 45 minutes.
Yields 4.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute minced onion and bell pepper in oil until brown.
Add hamburger, salt and pepper.
Brown this mixture and add cooked elbow macaroni and tomato juice.
Season with chili powder and cover top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
When cheese is melted, serve immediately.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in saucepan; cover.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Blend milk into flour gradually.
Stir into hot vegetables.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Yields 6 cups.
Calories 238 per cup.

title: salsa
directions: Blend together and chill. DELICIOUS!! Serve on crackers.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine cheese and butter.
Mix well.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: crowd pleaser casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower in slightly salted water.
Cook until slightly underdone.
Drain; set aside.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in 1-quart saucepan; add flour.
Blend well.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add Cheddar, Parmesan and salt.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Place vegetables in an ungreased 4-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with chopped ham.
Pour cheese sauce mixture over ham.
Toss bread crumbs with the melted butter.
Make a border of buttered bread crumbs around edge of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix together; fry in hot oil.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Arrange blueberries in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish. Sprinkle berries with lemon juice.
Mix sugar, flour, oats, oleo and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mixture on top of berries.
Microwave, uncovered, 12 to 14 minutes.

title: arroz con pollo pronto
directions: Brown chicken 5 minutes per side until golden; remove chicken from pan. Add onion and cook 5 minutes until golden. Add rice and 2 cups water and seasoning package.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, on top of rice. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat. Cover and cook 15 minutes; stir in peas. Cover and simmer 5 minutes until liquid is absorbed.

title: flank steak(aux champignous)
directions: Spread flank steak flat and make shallow diagonal cuts with a small sharp knife in a diamond shaped crisscross pattern (the way you might score the fat on a baked ham).
Do this on both sides. Sprinkle on steak some salt, fresh pepper and tenderizer.
Brown quickly on both sides in a hot nonstick skillet with a minimum of fat.
Add the wine, onion and mushrooms.
Cover and cook 2 minutes. Uncover and continue cooking until all the liquid has evaporated. Stir the mushrooms until they are lightly browned.
Slice the meat very, very thinly against the grain.
Serves 4, 216 calories each. Serve rare or medium rare, never overdone.

title: wassail punch(makes 12 servings)
directions: In a slow cooker or a large pot over low heat, combine apple cider, orange juice and lemon juice. Season with cloves, ginger and nutmeg. Bring to a simmer. If using a slow cooker, allow to simmer all day. Serve hot.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and boil sweet potatoes in enough water to cover until just tender.
As soon as they are cool enough, peel and cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and salt.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows the last 5 minutes.

title: crock-pot pork chops and stuffing
directions: Mix stuffing mix as directed on package. Place half of stuffing in lightly greased crock-pot. Spread half of undiluted soup on top of stuffing. Place pork chops on top. Spoon rest of stuffing on top. Spread rest of soup on top. Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into little balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast bread(servings:  10)
directions: Mix Bisquick, eggs, cheese, salt and pepper together in large bowl.
Brown sausage; drain.
Add to mixture.
Saute onion, yellow squash, zucchini and green pepper in butter, covered.
When vegetables are clear, add to mixture and stir until completely mixed.
Spread evenly into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, white syrup and melted butter.
Add well beaten eggs and mix.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° until done, about 35 to 45 minutes.
Shake pie until it won't shake in the middle.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of rectangular pan.
Heat 1/2 cup chocolate chips and margarine in microwave or in saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir mix, sugar, vanilla and eggs. Then stir in chocolate mixture.
Spread in pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle with marshmallows, nuts and remaining chips.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until marshmallows are light brown.
Cool.
Makes 30 bars.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into a greased bread pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken with mushroom and herb gravy
directions: Rinse and pat chicken dry with paper towels.
Line baking pan with aluminum foil.
Place chicken pieces in large casserole dish. Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour mushroom and herb gravy over chicken and return to oven at 400°.

title: molded seafood salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water, then add boiling water and salt.
Add seafood, celery and olives; mix well.
Add salad dressing and mayonnaise; blend thoroughly.
Chill until firm and serve on bed of endive or crisp lettuce.

title: orange trifle
directions: Cut cake into 1/2-inch slices.
Brush slices on both sides with orange juice.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time; add vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cloves and cinnamon. Add dry sifted mixture to apples and nuts, then add to cream mixture.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 55 or 60 minutes.

title: freezer cold slaw
directions: Pour 1 cup water over cabbage.
Add carrot, sweet pepper and salt.
Let stand 1 hour, then hand squeeze.
Boil vinegar and sugar together.
Add celery seed and mustard seed.
Pour over cabbage and put in refrigerator.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss with Sunny Dressing.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in gallon jar, add salt.
Cover with vinegar and let stand for 14 days.
Drain and slice cucumbers.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cut up into small pieces.
Thaw broccoli just enough to separate into small pieces.
Arrange broccoli on bottom of casserole dish and cover with chicken; set aside.
Heat soup and mayonnaise and stir well.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate nut pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, egg, pumpkin and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients.
Add nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: lemon-garlic round steak
directions: Place meat in shallow dish.
Heat oil.
Add garlic and lemon. Saute until lemon peel is lightly browned.
Pierce meat deeply at intervals with fork.
Pour hot oil over meat.
Place lemon and garlic pieces around steak.
Turn meat in marinade.
Cover. Marinate at room temperature for 1 to 2 hours or in refrigerator for 6 to 12 hours.
Turn meat 2 or 3 times.
Remove steak.
Reserve marinade.
Place steak on broiler rack.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 5 minutes until browned.
Turn; brown other side about 5 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture onto bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet on medium heat until crisp.
Drain bacon, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Crumble bacon; reserve 2 tablespoons.
Cook beans until tender; drain well.
Add mushrooms and onion to reserved 1/4 cup drippings in skillet.
Cook and stir on medium-high 10 minutes; drain.
Add bacon, hot cooked green beans and pepper; mix lightly.
Spoon into 2-quart serving dish. Melt cheese spread.
Pour over green bean mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved 2 tablespoons crumbled bacon.
Makes 10 servings.

title: seafood cakes
directions: Mix seafood, mayonnaise, green pepper, onion, dash of salt, pepper and 1/2 cup bread crumbs together.
Shape into hamburger size patties.
Cover with egg, then coat with flour and then breadcrumbs.
Saute slowly until brown in liquid oil.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cut up and brown about 1 1/2 pounds of chicken on stove.
Take 1 can of cream of chicken soup and 1 can of water; bring to a boil and add 2 c. minute rice.
Remove from the heat and let set for 5 minutes.
Spread rice in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Place chicken on rice, skin side up.
Cover with foil and bake in the oven for 1 hour at 325°.

title: herbed chicken stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry oil, garlic and onion; remove onion.
Stir-fry chicken, 1/2 at at time, for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Stir-fry zucchini for 5 minutes.
Add bouillon mixture and tomatoes.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add chicken and onion. Cook 1 minute. Serve over rice or with chow mein noodles, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: glass candy
directions: Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
After it boils, stir in drops of food coloring.

Insert thermometer and stop stirring. When it reaches 280°, turn down to low heat, stir in flavor. Bring to 300° and remove from heat and pour into greased molds (for suckers) or you may pour out onto greased cookie sheet and break up like glass.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Blend sugar, Crisco and egg yolks.
Alternately add 3/4 cup buttermilk and flour.
Add chocolate and water and 1/4 cup buttermilk and soda.
Add egg whites, gently folding into batter. Makes 3 large layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust and chill about 2 or 3 hours before putting on cherry pie filling.

title: gumdrop bar
directions: Thoroughly mix flour, gumdrops and pecans; set aside. Beat eggs with water until foamy. Gradually add brown sugar, beating until light. Beat in cinnamon and salt. Stir in gumdrop mixture. Spread mixture evenly in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° until done, 15 to 20 minutes. While still warm, spread with Orange Icing and cut into 2-inch squares. Remove from pan. Garnish with sliced gumdrops, if desired. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: skillet vegetable soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Puree bananas.
Add to mixture with beaten eggs.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: porcupines en casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, plus 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and garlic powder.
Form into balls and place in greased casserole.
Combine soup, water, catsup, remaining salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; pour over meat.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and stir in cheese.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
I use 2 tablespoons of mix in coffee size mug. I use 20 1/4 grams saccharines.
Sweet 'N Low works well also.

title: sausage bread
directions: Beat together egg and milk.
Add Bisquick mix, sausage and cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Put in a greased loaf pan or pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
This is great for breakfast.
Serve warm.

title: orange-glazed yams
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange potato slices in buttered baking dish.
In small bowl, combine orange-juice concentrate, sugar and bacon.
Pour juice mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake until heated through, about 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: north carolina spiedes(excellent recipe)
directions: Marinate chicken in the mixture for 24 hours.
Put chicken on skewers and grill.
Serve on sliced Italian bread!! Easy and delicious.

title: fort worth corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Add oleo and set aside. Mix corn and soup; add rice.
Pour into a buttered casserole. Cover with cheese and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: barber poles
directions: Wrap bacon slices diagonally around breadsticks.
Coat with cheese.
Arrange in microwave-safe baking dish lined with paper towels.
Microwave on High for 4 1/2 to 6 minutes or until bacon is cooked through.
Roll in remaining cheese.
Makes 10 breadsticks.

title: crab hors d'oeuvre
directions: With biscuit cutter, cut 2 medium and 2 small rounds from each slice of bread.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Spread mixture on bread rounds.
Garnish with parsley, slice of olive, pimento or anything colorful.
Place in a 350° oven until mixture bubbles.
Serve hot.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13 pan that you want to serve the dessert in.
Stir in flour and nuts, press into pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375 degrees.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, 4x sugar and half of whipped topping, spread over crust.
Mix 2 packages of instant chocolate pudding with 3 cups of milk.
Blend the pudding and milk for 2 minutes, let set for a few minutes then spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Spread on the rest of the whipped topping.

title: chicken pudding
directions: On wax paper, combine 1/3 cup of the flour, 1/4 tsp. of the salt, and the pepper.
Coat chicken with this mixture.
In a deep, 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat the oil over moderately high heat.
Add the chicken and cook for 4 minutes on each side or until browned.
Add the stock and bring to a boil.
Lower the heat, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes.
Transfer to a buttered 13 X 9 X 3 inch baking dish reserving the stock.

title: indian pudding
directions: Combine cornmeal, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Scald milk and pour over mixture.
Stir well, then add molasses and raisins.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Stir twice during early baking.
Set oven at 375°.
Time:
1 1/4 hours.
This is an old, old recipe.

title: country company potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; peel and grate.
For best results, let potatoes cool before grating.
Heat soup and butter; add cheese, sour cream and onions.
Combine with potatoes in casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake 45 minutes uncovered at 350°.

title: hamburger helper
directions: Brown the ground meat. Add the remaining ingredients.
Let cook until all water is absorbed.
Stir occasionally.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In blender, combine pineapple juice, sugar and flour.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Top with cracker crumbs and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Grind carrots, pepper, onion and pimento.
Add to cooled jello and then add 1 pound cottage cheese and 1 cup salad dressing. Refrigerate.

title: baked potatoes stuffed with vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: charles cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Bake in greased pan at 400° about 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Grease bottom and side of 15 x 10 x 1 inch pan.
Prepare first four ingredients in large bowl, then press into pan. Bake 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Combine eggs, syrup, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Spread on crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until set.
Makes 48 bars.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients to a soft stage.
Place a drop of mixture into ice cold water.
It should form a soft ball, then add vanilla, marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Pour into pan and cool.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add pineapple juice and allow to cool, then add cream. Chill in refrigerator until it reaches the mushy stage. Add other ingredients and mix well. Put in bowl and refrigerate.

title: pineapple-banana cake
directions: Sift together into bowl flour, soda, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.
Make well in center.
Add to dry ingredients the vanilla, oil, pineapple, banana, nuts and eggs.
Stir; don't beat. Pour into greased floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.
Can frost or serve plain.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Mix milk and next 6 ingredients.
Slowly stir into the eggs. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set in a pan 1/2 full of hot water.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour, stirring 1 or 2 times during first 30 minutes.
Inserted knife, near edge, comes out clean when pudding is done.
Serves 6.

title: grandma's rice pudding
directions: Cook rice.
Mix milk, sugar, raisins and rice together.
Pour into a baking dish.
Top with cinnamon.
Bake at 325° until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Don't bake too long, it will dry out.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Melt margarine and combine with other ingredients.
Stir in bowl without using mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Combine ingredients.
With spoon, stir flour mixture into carrot mixture, just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin tins, which have been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked vidalias
directions: Slice in half, wash and peel.
Place in baking dish with 1 tablespoon butter on each half.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until tender.
May cover with cheese, bacon, etc.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, oil and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Mix in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
