Turn mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Yield: 6 servings. Carbohydrate 18 g, protein 19 g, fat 18 g, calories 310.
One serving = 1 bread starch exchange, 2 meat medium fat exchange, 2 fat exchange, 1/4 milk exchange.

title: grandma's jello salad
directions: Cook slowly until marshmallows melt--stir constantly so it won't stick.
Cool completely.
Fold into this mixture, 1 carton sm. curd cottage cheese (smaller sized carton), and 1 envelope whipped Dream Whip.
Pour into a mold and chill until set (will also work in a pan).

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
To serve: Place 2 tablespoons of mix in a cup, add 1 cup of boiling water and stir well.
Store mix in an airtight container.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: school rolls
directions: Mix yeast, water and sugar.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and dry milk.
Cut in shortening.
Add liquid.
Mix all ingredients well.
Set aside and let rise for about 15 minutes.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Divide mix into two 9 x 13-inch pans and bake approximately 15 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes, then invert one layer onto cooling rack.
Cool cakes completely.

title: chocolate amaretto torte
directions: Chop chocolate.
Cut cake lengthwise into 3 layers.
Sprinkle with Amaratto on each layer.
Cream Ricotta, sugar and vanilla. Add chocolate and spread onto 2 bottom layers.

title: cornmeal baked chicken
directions: Combine cornmeal and spices; dip chicken in milk, then coat in cornmeal mixture.
Place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle margarine over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Put in bottles.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Heat vinegar and honey in heavy small saucepan until honey is dissolved.
Pour into bowl and cool.
Whisk in mayonnaise, mustard, onion, parsley and salt.
Gradually whisk in oil.
Cover and refrigerate.
Can be prepared 3 days ahead.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dressing.

title: long boy cheeseburger
directions: Cut bread loaves into halves lengthwise.
Mix all ingredients (except for cheese) together and spread the mixture over the bread to edges.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done. Remove from oven and add cheese strips, using the pattern of your choice.
Return to oven for about 5 minutes until cheese has melted to your desire.
tags: several strips of your favorite cheese

title: meat loaf #2
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl, except tomato paste.
Put 1/2 can of tomato paste in mix and make into a loaf.
Place loaf in casserole dish.
Cover loaf with the other 1/2 can of tomato paste.
Place in a 350° oven and cook for 1 hour.

title: shrimp scampi with pasta
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons of butter and the olive oil in 2-quart saucepan until tender but not brown.
Add water and instant bouillon, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil!
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 12 to 15 minutes or until reduced by 2/3rds.
Add shrimp; simmer covered for 5 minutes or until done.
Add pasta and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Add cheese and toss to mix well.

title: easy cream cheese clouds
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed on electric mixer.
Gradually add heavy cream.
Mix well.
Whip until thickened.
Using back of spoon, shape into 10 (3 1/2-inch) shells.
Place on wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Freeze 2 hours. When ready to serve, fill with cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: oven dill potatoes
directions: Add all spices together in a large covered bowl.
Coat potato cubes in vegetable oil and add to spices.
Cover and shake until potatoes are well coated.
Spread onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until brown.
Turn once during baking.

title: flop cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add biscuit mix.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: carnival popcorn
directions: Go to the store and buy your favorite boxed mix and follow directions.
Come out of the kitchen and say "they're finally done."

title: mexi-chili casserole
directions: Set aside 1 cup chips and 1/2 cup cheese.
Combine everything else in 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle top with remaining chips and some more cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: goldies relish
directions: Chop fine first 4 ingredients.
Pour salt over; cover with ice and let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Mix remaining 6 ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Heat to boiling; lower temperature and simmer for 3 minutes.
Pack in hot jars. Process for 5 minutes, if desired.
Will keep without processing.

title: super bowl pizza
directions: With a low skillet, brown meat. Pour off excess grease. Dice cheese and add to sausage, plus seasoning to taste. Spread on rye bread. Put these on cookie sheet and brown at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Place rice in bottom of a medium size pan.
Lay chicken breasts on top.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with water and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle package of dried onion soup on top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 2 hours in a 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: ranch style potatoes
directions: Cook
bacon
in
a 12-inch Dutch oven until brown.
Add chopped
onion.
Saute
until
clear.
Add sliced potatoes and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, stirring occasionally until tender; put 12 coals on top and on bottom.

title: fruit custard pie
directions: Line 8 or 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Stew fruit (dried apples are best) in small amount of water.
When tender, mash and add sugar.
Cool.
Pour into pastry and spread evenly.
Make custard of eggs, beaten with sugar.
Slowly add milk, mixing well. Add melted butter and extract.
Pour over fruit.
Bake in a 425° oven for 12 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until custard is set.
Let cool before cutting.
Delicious!

title: popcorn peanut brittle
directions: Spread popped corn on large (at least 17 x 12 x 2-inch) buttered pan.
Sprinkle peanuts over top.
Slowly melt sugar in heavy frying pan, stirring constantly.
When sugar is golden brown, stir in margarine, vanilla and soda.
Pour in a fine stream over popcorn and peanuts.
Cool; break into bite size pieces.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine and shortening.
Beat well.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Sift flour and soda together; add alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in carefully, the beaten egg whites.
Bake for 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: soft sandwich buns
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast and 1/2 teaspoon sugar in 1/4 cup warm water; let stand until foamy, 5 to 10 minutes.

Add 1 cup water, milk and 2 cups flour. Stir vigorously until batter is smooth. Cover and let rise until light and spongy, about 30 minutes. Stir in shortening, 1/4 cup sugar and salt. Add remaining flour gradually until stiff dough is formed. On floured surface, knead dough until smooth and elastic, 5 to 10 minutes. Place in a greased bowl; turn to coat surface. Cover and let rise until doubled, 60 to 90 minutes. Shape into 2 inch balls by tucking ends under and flattening slightly. Place 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise until almost doubled. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash.
Combine all ingredients.
Put on topping.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Wash roast and place in Dutch oven with soup, onion mix and water. Bake covered at 375° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Then add peeled potatoes and carrots. Bake for additional 1 1/2 hours or until all is tender. (May also slice onions and add when adding other vegetables.)

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water and stir until dissolved. Put in refrigerator to cool until partly congealed. Add the lemon juice and whip. Fold evaporated milk into jello mixture. Butter a 9 x 13 inch cake pan. Line with graham cracker crumbs and pour filling over it. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over top of filling.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine onion and bell pepper with soups.
Add chicken and enchilada sauce.
Stir well, adding a handful of the grated cheese to the mixture.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream shortening well with white and brown sugars. Add eggs, blending well. Stir in apples. Sift together flour, baking powder and all dry ingredients. Add to apple mixture and blend well. Add soda to warm water and blend into batter. Add vanilla and nuts. Spread batter into loaf pan or 4 small pans. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: hot wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in large kettle and simmer 10 minutes. Serve hot or chill and serve cold.
This is wonderful for diabetics.

title: tomato meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 3 tablespoons catsup.
Pack in a greased 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Spread remaining catsup on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Gravy may be made from pan juices, if desired.
Ground lamb or veal may be used in place of beef.

title: company chicken for everyday
directions: If chicken not boneless, remove skin.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle generously with garlic and paprika.
In a bowl, mix soup with whipping cream until smooth.
Pour over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes (should be lightly brown and bubbly).
Best served with white rice, using soup as gravy.
For more people, add extra chicken, and double the soup and cream.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut and nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
In double boiler, put cream cheese and margarine; melt.
Then add 1 box powdered sugar.
Pour cake mix over coconut and nuts.
Then pour cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar on top.
Bake according to directions on cake mix box.
Very good and easy.

title: pastry
directions: Cut shortening into flour until fine.
Beat egg and add vinegar, while stirring briskly.
Add about 2/3 cup ice water. Mix the ingredients together until a soft dough (may need more water).
Let chill until the next day or several hours.
Roll out into assorted pie pans.
May freeze some until needed.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine and mix with all ingredients.	Pour into 9x13 baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into crock-pot that has been lightly greased.
Cut thin slices of cheese and place on top. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake for 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat for 25 minutes in saucepan or in a 300° oven.

title: famous lemon pie of the sunlight hotel
directions: Mix together cornstarch and sugar. Cover with (grated) rind and juice of lemons. Add (beaten) yolks of eggs, then add boiling water.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat 6 tablespoons sugar into them. Spread over lemon mixture, taking care to seal in filling completely.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until top is light brown.

title: baked rice with sausage
directions: In large skillet, cook sausage until almost done. Add celery, onion and pepper. Cook until tender and drain. In large saucepan, bring water to boil; add dry soup mix. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes until noodles are tender. Stir in canned soup, rice and sausage mixture. Mix well. Transfer to greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish or pan. Cover with foil and bake 40 minutes. Then uncover and bake 15 minutes. If desired, sprinkle bread crumbs on top during last 15 minutes (we omit). Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: lucille's zucchini recipe
directions: In a large skillet, melt oleo.
Add onion, green pepper, corn (if using fresh, cut off the cob) and zucchini.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
If using canned corn, add now with basil and pepper. Heat thoroughly.
Add cheese; heat again.
Serve garnished with sliced tomato.

title: frosted chews
directions: Place sugar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Stir to combine. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until it boils.
Remove from heat at very first sign of boiling.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add cereal and stir until coated.
Press mixture evenly into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together in double boiler or put in microwave for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Spread over bars.
Can substitute Rice Krispies for cereal.

title: grandma stewart's nutty fingers
directions: Mix and make into rolls the size of a finger.
Bake 20 minutes in a medium oven.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: waldorf red velvet cake(this cake is really red; great for valentine's day!)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until fluffy.
Add the vanilla.
Add the eggs one at a time and beat about 1 minute each. Mix the cocoa and food color into a paste and add this paste to the creamed mixture.
Add the flour, salt and buttermilk alternately to the creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Mix the vinegar and soda together (they will fizz) and add to the batter.
Bake in two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Dump all dry ingredients into large dishpan (enamel kind). Mix bacon drippings, Worcestershire sauce, melted oleo, garlic salt, seasoned salt, hot sauce and Tabasco sauce in small mixing bowl; pour over dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in same large dishpan at 225°.
Stir about every 15 minutes.

title: ye ole waterford apple cake
directions: Combine apples, sugar and cinnamon; let stand.
Cream butter and sugar until smooth; add eggs.
Alternate flour (combined with baking powder) and orange juice; add vanilla.
Batter should be on the thick side.
In humid weather, you may not need all of the juice.
Add nuts.

title: corn and frito salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, add cheese and Fritos.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, apple pie filling and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Do not remove from pan until completely cooled.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Use a 10-inch tube pan, greased.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: imitation rice-a-roni
directions: Use same method of One Knuckle Rice.
In pan, saute thin spaghetti in one tablespoon margarine.
Add rice, water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil.
Cover and turn down to low.
Cook 20 minutes.
Fluff rice mixture and add margarine.
This is better than the real thing and best of all is lower in fat and salt content.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Scald together the margarine and milk.
Add to the remaining ingredients.
Have your baking pan greased and floured and the oven preheated.
Takes 5 minutes to mix! Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Needs no icing.

title: meat-sa pie
directions: Mix together hamburger, milk, crumbs and garlic salt.
Put into 9-inch pie plate.
Combine pizza sauce, 1 cup of shredded cheese, mushrooms, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Spread on top of meat mixture.
Bake 25 minutes in a 375° oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of shredded cheese over top. Return to oven for about 5 minutes or until cheese on top is melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and butter.
Cook 20 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.
Remove.
Add marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
If desired, add nuts or peanut butter or coconut (or add all).

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a baking pan or dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Mix onions and cabbage in bowl.
Brown almonds and sesame seeds in 2 Tbsp. butter.	Add remaining ingredients to almonds and sesame seeds and heat.
Break Top Ramen noodles over cabbage in bowl. Pour hot mixture over cabbage and toss.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine melted butter, salt and garlic salt.
Dip chicken pieces in.
Mix together bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Roll chicken dipped in butter mixture in crumb mixture.
Lay on cookie sheet and bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine.
Add flour, milk, cheese, chilies and Tabasco to taste.
Serve with corn chips.

title: pork carnitas empanadas
directions: Mix the masa, oil, salt and water in a bowl. Knead briefly until very smooth. Shape into a ball and reserve.

title: jiffy beans and franks
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; spoon into a lightly greased, shallow 2-quart casserole.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap. Fold back a small edge of wrap to allow steam to escape. Microwave at High 8 to 9 minutes, stirring once.
Add frankfurters.
Microwave at High 8 to 9 minutes, stirring once. Yield: 6 servings.

title: beef with broccoli
directions: Remove any fat and cut across the grain into thin slices.
Cut the broccoli spears and section into individual pieces.
Heat the wok until hot and add the oil.
Wait until the oil is hot and add the beef and stir until beef changes color.
Add the vegetables and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove the contents to drain the excess oil. Heat the wok and add first mixture.
Add the drained beef and vegetables and stir lightly.
Once the contents begin to boil the sauce will thicken.
This is due to the cornstarch in the beef. Toss lightly and remove to serve.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper and carrot in a large container. Heat vinegar, sugar and spices.
Cool slightly.
Pour over the veggies.
Mix together; cool.
Put in freezer containers; freeze. May chop or shred vegetables.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients real fine.
Mix bacon bits, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add to chopped ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add other ingredients. Pour into greased pan and bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.

title: sunshine muffins(lo-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat egg with egg whites.
Add margarine, sugar and applesauce and beat well.
Stir in carrots and pineapple.

title: relish
directions: Grind vegetables; sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand at least 4 hours.
Rinse and drain; then add the remaining ingredients to the ground vegetable mixture.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: custard pudding(bouillant lait)
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sugar slowly.
Add a little milk at a time to make creamy.
Put evaporated milk, vanilla and milk in saucepan.
Let get real warm but not boiling.
Add egg mixture slowly and mix well.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup warm water, mixing well.
Add cornstarch to milk, stirring constantly.
After mixing well, slowly turn up heat and let come to a boil stirring constantly.
Cook until as thick as desired.

title: quick chicken - tasting is believing
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in butter or margarine. Drain chicken on paper towels.
Place in baking dish. Mix together salad dressing, soup mix and cranberry sauce.
Pour over chicken. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli as directed.
Mix all ingredients and put into greased casserole dish.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing mix.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Separate rolls into triangles and arrange to fit pizza pan.
Layer sausage, potatoes and cheese. Beat rest of ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pink shady
directions: Just before serving, in 2 quart pitcher, combine lemonade and beer, stirring until blended.
Serve over ice and garnish with lemon slice.

title: marie's cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat well and frost cake.
Add additional pecans on top.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add pineapple. Add flour that has been sifted with baking powder. Add small amounts at a time alternately with milk.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan. Place in cold oven. Turn oven to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back when touched lightly.
Let stand for 10 minutes in pan.

title: oriental salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: When you read this, you will know why you only serve this once a year.
It should be mixed in nothing less than the kitchen sink!

title: thai-style pork kabobs(diabetic)
directions: Combine soy sauce, lime juice, chili oil, garlic and ginger. Reserve 1/3 cup mixture for dipping sauce.
Set aside.
Cut tenderloin lengthwise into halves and crosswise in 4-inch slices. Cut slices in 1/2-inch strips.
Add to soy sauce; toss and coat. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes longer.
To prevent sticking, spray grid with nonstick cooking spray.
Prepare grill.
Remove pork from marinade.
Place pork strips, bell peppers and onion on 8 to 10-inch skewers.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes, turning one at a time. (One vegetable, 1 1/2 starch, 2 meat, 248 calories from fat 16%, 4 fat grams, 229 protein and 30 g carbohydrates.)

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Debone chicken.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Place a few strips of chicken at widest part of crescent roll.
Place some cheese on top of chicken.
Then roll crescent roll together and fold end up. Place in casserole dish.
Repeat until all rolls are formed.
In bowl, pour cream of chicken soup and one can water.
Mix well. Pour in casserole dish with chicken rolls until soup is halfway up the sides of chicken rolls.
Bake at 350° until tops are golden brown.
Soup will make gravy to serve over rice or potatoes.

title: marie's cornbread for dressing
directions: Sift Jiffy mix and corn meal together.
Combine dry ingredients and mix well with water.
Pour mixture into greased pan.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: mystery dip
directions: *I rarely use the salt, mostly the powders, or the garlic.

title: macadamia nut and white chocolate cookies
directions: Position rack in center of oven and preheat oven to 350°. Cover 2 baking sheets with parchment paper or aluminum foil.
In medium bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, beat butter for 30 to 45 seconds with electric mixer; set on low.
Butter should be creamy.
Gradually add sugars to batter and beat at medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes or until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well between each addition.
Add vanilla.
Using wooden spoon, stir in flour mixture.
Add chocolate chunks and nuts; stir until well combined.

title: stuffed garlic bread
directions: Cut a "V" shape top out of entire loaf; save.
Remove all bread from interior, leaving crust shell intact.
Tear into large chunks.
Brown bread and garlic in butter.
Drizzle with a little olive oil while browning.
In a large bowl, mix bread mixtures, cheeses, sour cream and pepper, mixing well.
Spoon mixture back into crust shell.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Replace top of bread.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and hot throughout (about 25 minutes).

title: 5 can casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix 5 cans in casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add beaten eggs, salt, vanilla and soda in water and mashed bananas with flour; mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pan in 350° oven about 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pickled vegetables
directions: Combine sugar, salt and water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add vinegar.
Cool; pour over cut vegetables at least 2 hours before serving.
May use cauliflower, carrot, cucumber, radish, celery, round onion, broccoli.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (make sure spinach is as dry as possible before adding).
Let set few hours or overnight.
Carve out loaf of bread and fill with dip, using pieces from loaf to dip.
Also use breadsticks or vegetables to dip.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk and blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill at least 3 hours.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients.
Mix rest of ingredients together well.
Add browned meat mixture.
Put into greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
At this point, you may refrigerate and bake the next morning.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until lightly browned.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: yummy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Blend condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip and pineapple.
Blend well.
Chill before serving.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and water in bowl on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until melted.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Beat egg whites in another large bowl with electric mixer on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Gently stir into batter. Pour into three (9-inch) round cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched in center.
Immediately run spatula between cakes and sides of pans.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal and salt together in large bowl. Pour approximately 2 cups boiling water over dry ingredients. Mix well. After mixture cools slightly, shape mixture into golf ball sized balls, one at a time. You must wet your hands with water before you make each ball. Flatten the ball with your fingers. Fry in skillet (preferably cast-iron) with about 1/2-inch of hot oil. Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: crackerjack cookies
directions: Cream soft butter and sugars.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients with cooked, drained squash.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; form into walnut size balls for hors d'oeuvres or larger if for a meal.
Brown in the butter or margarine.
When brown and almost cooked, add the pineapple juice, pineapple chunks, vinegar, sugar and soy sauce.
Heat through. Combine the cornstarch and water; blend in with the mixture in the skillet.
Cook until thickened.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: In small bowl mix flour and sugar.
Pour pineapple into a baking dish, sprinkle flour and sugar mixture over pineapple; then grated cheese.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Sift flour with soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream the butter and add sugar; mix well.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add vanilla and lemon extract, then add the buttermilk.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: baked potato balls
directions: Mix potatoes and egg well.
Shape into balls with ice cream dipper and roll in crushed corn flakes.
Make a depression on the top of each ball and dot with butter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or put under broiler until brown.

title: toad-in-the-hole
directions: Mix and blend flour, eggs, milk and seasonings to make smooth creamy batter.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°. Prick sausage; cook in heavy covered skillet to which 2 tablespoons of water have been added for about 2 minutes.
Remove cover and continue cooking until water has evaporated and sausage turns brown.

title: ham loaf
directions: Remove cover last 10 minutes to brown top.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for approximately 2 hours.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Combine apple juice, spices and cornstarch and microwave until cornstarch dissolves.
Place apples in bottom crust and pour apple juice over it.
Put top crust on and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set for at least 2 hours or until cooled.

title: peach bavarian
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 2/3 cup juice.
Chop peaches into small pieces; set aside.
In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in reserved syrup.
Chill until slightly thickened. Stir extract into Cool Whip.
Gently fold in gelatin mixture. Fold in peaches.
Pour into an oiled 6-cup mold.
Chill overnight. Unmold.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: texas fresh grapefruit cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with grapefruit juice, beginning and ending with flour.
Gradually add milk.
Stir in grapefruit rind and vanilla extract; mix well.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
Spread Grapefruit Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: spiced apple simmer
directions: In a 5 - quart dutch oven, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 20 minutes. Remove and discard spices.
Serve hot.
Yields 30
3/4 cups.

title: chili and corn casserole
directions: Whirl the corn in an electric blender with 2 or 3 tablespoons of reserved corn liquid for a few seconds; then add to the chilies in mixing bowl.
Add the butter, eggs, corn meal, salt, sour cream and diced cheese and mix all thoroughly.
Pour the mixture into a buttered casserole and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes to an hour or until golden brown and firm to the touch. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers to fine crumbs. Add next four ingredients, mixing well.
Form into balls and roll in flaked coconut.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix margarine and flour.
Stir in pecans.
Put mixture into 9 x 12-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool. Cream together the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 3 cups whipped topping.
Spread pudding on top of cherries.
Add 3 cups of whipped topping.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 1/4 cup chocolate on top.
Refrigerate until served.

title: loaded potato soup
directions: Dice unpeeled red potatoes into 1/2 inch cubes.
Place in a large Dutch oven, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Let boil for 10 minutes or until 3/4 cooked.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello and water. Add strawberries. Stir well. Add banana, pineapple and nuts.
Pour half
of the mixture in a long Pyrex dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream on top and remaining mixture. Chill until firm.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats, chocolate pieces and nuts.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Crush Ritz crackers.
Add chopped pecans and vanilla flavoring.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff and gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Mix ingredients of both bowls together.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
After pie cools, top with Dream Whip.
This pie is chewy and moist and very rich.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes (plain mashed, no butter, milk or salt added) and confectioners sugar. Stir in coconut, vanilla and salt; blend well. Press into 1 large or 2 small pans so that candy will be about 1/2-inch thick. Melt chocolate over hot water. (Do not allow water to boil. If chocolate gets too hot, it may be streaky when hardened.) Pour chocolate on top of candy. Cool and cut into squares.

title: low-fat fettuccini
directions: Blend flour and margarine in a saucepan.
Cook for several minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice, parsley, black pepper and cheese.
Stir until well blended.
Serve over cooked fettuccini.
Top with additional grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli-onion quiche
directions: Prick pie crust and bake 5 minutes at 450°.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
alternate layers of broccoli pieces and grated cheese-onion mixture.
Beat eggs and all other remaining ingredients together and pour over broccoli-cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with rest of Parmesan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 minutes more or until set.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf. Serves 4.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: berry-melon salad
directions: Combine juices, cornstarch, vegetable oil and honey in a saucepan, stirring well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in poppy seed.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Peel cantaloupes and cut each melon into four 3/4-inch slices.
Place slices on individual salad plates. Combine strawberries and honeydew melon balls.
Spoon 1/2 cup strawberry mixture over each cantaloupe slice.
Spoon poppy seed mixture evenly over fruit.

title: st. joseph's bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter, anise seed and salt like a pie crust, then add remaining ingredients.
Knead.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and braid into 10 small loaves (start at center and braid both ways).
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine persimmons and milk and run through colander.
Add soda and brown sugar, to taste.
Add eggs and enough flour to make a thin batter.
Bake in greased shallow baking dish at 350° until set like custard (1 hour or more).

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until very creamy and smooth.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube cake pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a rolling boil sugar and milk.
Add crackers, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until thick (about 5 minutes).
Spread in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: macaroni salad(serves 8)
directions: After cooking macaroni, rinse and drain well and save. Combine last 5 ingredients in small bowl.
Stir and save. Combine remaining ingredients together with macaroni and mix well, then add small bowl sauce and stir until all mixed very well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put the sweet potatoes in a large mixing bowl and mash with a wooden spoon or a potato masher.
Set aside.
Combine the eggs, sugar, spices, salt, lemon zest and cream in a small bowl; whisk until combined.
Pour this mixture into the sweet potatoes; stir until thoroughly combined.
Add the butter; mix well.
Pour into the pie shell and bake for an hour, or until filling is set and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let cool completely before slicing.

title: crab casserole
directions: Grease pan.
Melt butter and saute onion and mushrooms for 3 minutes.
Add crab, sherry and salt.
Blend flour and milk and add to skillet.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in cheese.
Put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs and oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil the chicken breasts.
Remove meat from bones and cut up. In a large bowl, mix together the cut up chicken, rice and soups. Add milk until creamy.
Bake in oven at 375° to 400° until hot. May add crumbled bread topping and bake until brown.

title: low-fat spinach lasagna roll-ups(makes 4 to 5 servings)
directions: Mix together the spinach, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and egg. Spread 1 cup sauce in bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish (sprayed with Pam). Spread a scant 1/2 cup spinach mixture on each noodle. Roll up jelly roll style. Place roll-ups, seam side down in the dish. Cover with remaining sauce. Cover dish with foil. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: indian chole(garbanzo beans)
directions: *Mix 1/4 teaspoon cumin powder, 1/2 tsp. coriander powder, 1/8 teaspoon nutmeg powder and 1/8 teaspoon cloves = Garam Masala Indian.

title: crockpot mac & cheese
directions: Spray crock pot with cooking spray. Add macaroni. Mix in all ingredients except 1 cup cheese. Mix well. Top with remaining cheese. Cover; cook on low for 5-6 hours or until firm and golden brown. Do not uncover or stir until finished.

title: seafoam salad(serves 6)
directions: Heat pear juice.
Mix with lime jello and cool.
Finely chop pears.
Whip cream.
Whip cream cheese with milk or light cream. Gently mix cream cheese, jello and pears.
Fold in whipped cream. Chill several hours, preferably overnight.

title: vineyard leg of lamb
directions: With the tip of a knife, cut a dozen slits 1-inch deep all over the surface of the lamb; insert a sliver of garlic in each slit.
Cut a double thickness of cheesecloth about 16-inches wide and 20-inches long and drench it with 1/2 cup of the brandy.
Wrap the cloth around the lamb and cover with plastic wrap.
Marinate at room temperature about 2 hours.

title: chicken and green chili casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch strips.
Mix soups, onion and milk together.
Butter a 3 to 4-quart casserole.
Add a layer of soup mixture, layer of chicken and a layer of tortilla strips (adding all of the strips).
Top with chilies.
Add remaining soup mixture.
Top with cheese. Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 hour.

title: corn flakes cookie bar
directions: Melt chips.
Stir in peanut butter, then fold in the corn flakes.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cooled, cut into squares.

title: potted plant dessert
directions: Note:
Need one new medium-size plastic flower pot and some plastic or silk flowers.

title: unusual dumplings
directions: Boil chicken, remove from broth and debone the chicken, then return it to the broth.
Dampen flour tortillas and cut up with scissors to the size you want.
Coat with flour and place in boiling liquid with the chicken.
Season to taste.
Cook slowly for 15 to 20 minutes.
Be sure tortillas are covered with the liquid.
Stir, but not too often.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream the margarine and powdered sugar together.
Add the other ingredients. Shape in cylinders. Cook at 300° for 15 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: savory broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pastry crust for 8 to 10 minutes. Steam broccoli until tender; drain.
Saute onion and butter over medium heat until golden brown.
Add nutritional yeast; mix well. Simmer at low heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Place onion mixture on bottom of prebaked crust. Sprinkle with 3/4 grated cheese.
Top with broccoli.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Add rest of cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix tuna, milk and crumbs.
Beat eggs and add onions, parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Pack in a greased loaf pan.
Bake in oven for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil. Boil 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool.

title: peppered tuna nicoise
directions: Combine 1 teaspoon Parmesan cheese with flour.
Toss zucchini pieces in cheese mixture.
Place in shallow 2-quart microwave-safe casserole with lid.
Add chicken and toss.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring once or until chicken loses its pink color.
In small bowl combine bread crumbs and remaining 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle chicken and zucchini with bread crumb mixture.
Cover lightly with paper towel.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes until chicken is almost fully cooked. Spoon sauce over chicken and zucchini mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: mandarin napoleon liqueur lychee glaze
directions: Heat lychee juice and corn syrup to a rolling boil.
Cool until lukewarm, add lemon juice and liqueur.
Stir until blended. This can be spread over a cake or used as a glaze for pork, ham or chicken.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: In 6-quart kettle, put water, seasonings and parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Add fish chunks.
Simmer gently 10 to 12 minutes, depending on thickness of fish.
Remove fish with slotted spoon to serving platter.
Let set a few minutes to firm up.
Serve with melted butter for dipping.
Lemon juice may be added to butter.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apples and water in bottom of 10 x 6-inch glass baking dish.
Mix flour, sugars, cinnamon and salt in a bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream if desired.

title: nellie's hot dog sauce
directions: Mix well all ingredients together.
Simmer for 45 minutes, uncovered or in a slow cooker for 3 hours.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Blend tomatoes in blender. Set aside. Saute chopped onion and garlic in olive oil in a big pan.
Pour in tomatoes and stir.
Add basil and sugar to taste.
Simmer over medium heat for at least 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over 1 to 2 pounds of favorite pasta.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients in saucepan and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and mix until melted.
Then add vanilla extract, oatmeal and coconut or chopped nuts or both. Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes about 56 pieces, depending on size.

title: clouds at sunrise
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar.
Gradually add the sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in the crushed crackers and pecans.
Spread in well-buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack in pan.
Spread with whipped cream and top with cherry pie filling.
Good and rich.

title: chess pie
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Mix together well and pour in 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 300° to 350° for 55 minutes.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Sift flour.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup water.
Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Mix in bowl 1 cup sugar, fruit and 1/2 cup water.
Pour flour mixture over butter.
Pour fruit mixture over flour mixture.
Do not stir after placing in pan.
Crust will rise to top as it cooks.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornflakes and melted butter. Pour into baking dish. Top with mixture of cornflakes and melted butter. Bake at 400° for 1 hour, covered. Remove cover last 10 to 15 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine dry ingredients in paper bag.
Shake potatoes to coat.
Place potatoes in one layer in pan. Bake 1 hour, turning once, at 350°.
Great!

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears.
Use juice to make jello.
Cool.
Put pears, cream cheese and Cool Whip in blender.
Blend well and add cooled jello.
Pour into large bowl.
Refrigerate to set.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, fruit cocktail (including the juice), eggs, oil and coconut (if used).
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.
Do not underbake!.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.

title: creamy pea salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, stirring gently.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Stir in bacon and cashews.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Yields 4 servings.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain. Combine soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper,
and Worcestershire sauce; beat well. Layer carrots, bell pepper and onion. Pour sauce over this and marinate for 12 hours. Yield:
12 to 20 servings.

title: caviar canape
directions: Mix the eggs and the mayonnaise together in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix the cream cheese and sour cream together.
In an 8-inch spring-form pan, spread the egg mixture in the bottom. Sprinkle with the onion, then spread the sour cream mixture over top.
Chill for 3 hours or overnight.
To serve, sprinkle with caviar.

title: no cholesterol lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in water. Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour egg product into a small bowl.
Add about 1/4 cup hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Gradually return it to saucepan, stirring; blend well.
Add lemon juice and stir over low heat until very thick, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat; add lemon peel and margarine.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours until set.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Cook 2 hours, then add 1 cup cornstarch dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
Cook 1/2 hour longer.
Seal in hot jars.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: In large bowl, place chunks of tomato, green pepper and red onion.
Sprinkle generously with oregano and Italian seasoning. Douse liberally with red wine vinegar.
Crisscross with olive oil. Don't stir until serving time.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off wings and then cut wings in half.
Cook in oil until done.
Put wings in a bowl with lid or shaker bag.
Add oleo.
Sprinkle hot sauce and barbecue sauce (if you want) and shake until evenly distributed.
Use dressing as a dip.

title: great giblet gravy
directions: Blend cornstarch or flour into a small amount of broth.
Add to large amount.
Stir in giblets, chopped boiled eggs and neck meat.
Boil until slightly thickened.
Add seasonings and a little more broth if the gravy is too thick.

title: bologna salad
directions: Chop or dice bologna.
Add finely chopped celery, minced onion, pepper, sweet pickles, croutons and boiled eggs.
Add potato chips, mustard and salad dressing; mix well.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Measure first 4 ingredients in heavy saucepan and boil 1 minute on medium heat.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and beat until spreadable.
If it gets too thick, add 1 tablespoon milk and beat again.

title: sweet potato with orange
directions: Bake sweet potato for 1 hour or until tender.
Split the top open and scoop out the potato.
Mix with orange juice and nutmeg. Refill the jacket and serve.
Makes 1 serving.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Put between waxed paper and flatten with mallet or rolling pin.
Place 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese in middle of each chicken breast.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Season crumbs with salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt butter.
Roll chicken in butter, then in crumbs.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: almond delight dip
directions: Combine yogurt and almond extract in a small bowl; chill at least 1 hour.
Sprinkle chopped almonds and serve red and green apple slices.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: angel food delight
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 1/2 cups hot water; let set until starts setting, then whip.
Fold in whipping cream and berries.
Break cake into small pieces and fold all together.
Pour into cake pan and let set for 1/2 day in refrigerator.

title: no bake fudgy oat cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine oats and coconut; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine milk and butter.
Stir in sugar and cocoa; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Add oat mixture, stirring constantly; cook for 1 minute.
Remove from the heat; stir in vanilla.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 1 in. apart onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook until all ingredients are done, stirring occasionally. Simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: flavored crackers
directions: For each serving, make diagonal cuts in frankfurter, not cutting completely through.
Baste with cola-flavored carbonated beverage, pineapple preserves or mixture of 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons horseradish.
Baste while on grill until desired perfection.

title: peach crisp
directions: Pour peach mix in bottom of flat pan.
Sprinkle dry spice cake mix over top about 1/8 inch thick.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream when cool.

title: taco beef soup
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Drain fat.
Add water, seasoning mix, tomatoes, tomato sauce, corn and drained and rinsed kidney beans.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: nutty rice pilaf
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a large skillet; add pecans and saute 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove pecans, cover and set aside.
In same skillet, melt rest of butter; add onion and saute until tender.
Add rice and stir thoroughly to coat the grains.
Add chicken broth, salt (if needed), thyme and pepper. Cover and simmer 18 to 20 minutes until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed.
(Can be made ahead and refrigerated up to 24 hours.)

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat milk, sugar, salt and oil to lukewarm.
Add this to yeast mixture.
Blend in flour and mix well.
Dough will be soft.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Scrape out onto floured board.
Knead lightly.
Round up dough into ball and cut into 16 rolls.
Let rise 15 minutes on greased and floured pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven until lightly browned (approximately 30 minutes).

title: bean hot dish
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add meat and onions.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Works well in crock-pot.
Use any combination of beans.
Freezes well.

title: citrus punch
directions: Mix together in a large container.
Use mixture for ice rings if needed.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese.
Drain crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add to cottage cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: dorothy's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and bring to boil.
Very good on pork.

title: belgium waffles
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff; set aside.
Mix other ingredients and egg yolks, then add egg whites.
Bake in Belgium waffle iron.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add vanilla.
Mix together the dry ingredients and slowly add to butter mixture.
Add milk to batter, a small amount at a time.
Place apples in a buttered 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Add pecans and raisins, if desired.
Pour batter over the apple mixture and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean and the crust is a golden brown.

title: hot chicken saladwestboro, missouri
directions: In a 9 X 9 casserole dish, combine chicken, celery and almonds.
Blend onion, lemon juice, mayonaise and salt (pepper if desired).
Put into a greased casserole dish and top with cheese and crushed chips.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Mix cold water with corn meal.
Stir in boiling water and salt.
Cook, stirring often, until mixture thickens and boils. Cover and continue cooking over low heat for 20 minutes.
Pour into dish and cool.
Can be eaten like cereal with milk and sugar.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco and add water to make thick dough.
Knead well.
Break off handfuls and fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine egg with milk.
Whip gently.
Combine flour, cheese, paprika, salt and pepper.
Dip rinsed and dried chicken breasts individually into egg mixture and then roll in cheese mixture.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Melt cheese and butter.
Add shredded crab meat and chopped mushrooms.
Spoon on quartered, lightly toasted muffins.
Place under broiler until slightly browned.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: marvelous macaroni salad
directions: Cook
macaroni
until just done.
Drain well.
Toss with onions, sweet pepper and cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add salad dressing for desired consistency.

title: italian water ice
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and let cool to room temperature.
Add cream of tartar and lemon juice.
Mix; pour into large bowl and place in freezer for 2 hours.
Freeze until mushy, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add to mixture.
Continue freezing, stirring occasionally, until mixture has a snowy consistency.

title: honeyed carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cover and cook over low heat 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: fudge frosting
directions: In saucepan, bring cocoa, milk and margarine to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add nuts if desired.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls and cool.
Mix salad dressing, softened cream cheese and Ranch dressing; spread on rolls.
Top with cut up broccoli, cauliflower, peppers, mushrooms and carrots.
Sprinkle with dill seed, then refrigerate.

title: peanut munch and crunch
directions: Before you cook candy,	put real chocolate morsels in a double boiler
to melt.
In
heavy
saucepan
mix
first	six ingredients.
(If you use
a candy thermometer, put in place.) Boil, stirring often, to
hard
crack
stage
(about
285°) or until a small mixture in cold water becomes brittle.
Take pan off and stir in baking	soda.
Pour on a greased cookie sheet. Spread very thin.	Take
the
chocolate morsels that have been melted and spread half of
the

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Add celery, onions, soy sauce and water. Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add 2 cans drained bean sprouts, 1 can sliced water chestnuts and 1 can sliced mushrooms.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Serve over cooked rice or Chinese noodles.

title: french bread
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar in electric mixer at low speed. Add some flour to dough before adding salt.
Gradually add flour until sides of mixer are clean.
Add a little oil! The dough should be stiff.
Mix for 10 minutes.
Let dough rise.
Make loaves.
Line pans with cornmeal.
Let rise.
Make diagonal slits across loaves halfway through rising.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Makes 3 or 4 loaves.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Combine chicken, salad dressing mix and cream cheese in a mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer until blended. Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Cover and chill.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
If a milder taste is desired, reduce horseradish and Tabasco.

title: country company potatoes
directions: Heat 1/2 cup oleo and cream of chicken soup.
Add onion, cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Add potatoes and mix. Put in 9 x 15-inch pan.
Top with corn flake crumbs and melted 2 tablespoons oleo, that have been mixed together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: belly buttons
directions: Mix together in large container, stirring once or twice before serving.

title: mom's stroganoff
directions: Saute beef and onion; drain.
Put beef and onion in large pot. Place uncooked noodles on top.
Mix all remaining ingredients. Pour over noodles and meat; do not stir! Bring to a slow boil, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until the noodles are tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper, onion powder and any other seasonings you like; set aside.
Put rice, soups, water and onion in
a 9 x 12-inch pan; mix well.
Place chicken pieces on top in single layer.
Cover with foil and bake 45 to 50 minutes or until rice and chicken are done.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more or until chicken is lightly browned.
Bake at 400°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Mix in dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Stir in crushed banana. Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil together 5 minutes the brown sugar, syrup, salt and margarine.
Stir while boiling.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and baking soda.
Grease pan.
Pour over corn and mix.
Spread in pan and bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Cool and package.

title: oven fried drumsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wipe chicken legs with damp paper towel. In clean bag, combine flour, corn flake crumbs, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and garlic.
Dip chicken in egg a couple at a time, then shake in bag to coat with flour mixture.
Arrange in greased pan.
Pour melted margarine over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Remove foil, increase heat to 450° and bake 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: meat loaf hamburger patties
directions: Mix well and make patties.
Put in skillet and fry until done; drain grease.
Take 1 cup tomato juice and sugar; mix together. Pour over hamburger patties.
Cover; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mushroom and bacon bites
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Cook until tender. Stir in bread crumbs, parsley, thyme, sage, walnuts and seasonings to taste.
Stretch out the bacon slices on a board and flatten. Divide mushroom mixture and place a portion on each slice and roll up like a jelly roll.
Arrange on a flat dish.
Sprinkle oil over them and bake 20 to 25 minutes in 375° oven.

title: fruited picnic slaw
directions: Combine pineapple and oranges with shredded cabbage.

title: irene's baked schrod
directions: Marinate cod fillet in a mixture of milk, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and a dash of salt and pepper. Remove after an hour. Blend paprika with oil and brush on fish, then roll in bread crumbs. Put fish in baking pan. Brush with butter and pour over wine. Bake in hot 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes. Do not overcook!

title: crabmeat-cheese canapes
directions: Melt cheese and butter together.
Add onion and crabmeat. Mix together.
Cool.
Spread on party rye.
Brown in broiler.

title: garden pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with dill weed and dried onion.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread on crust after it cools.
Add chopped tomato, peppers, onion, black olive bits and celery, all chopped fine.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: sweet-sour bean salad
directions: Drain and wash the three cans of beans, then combine with the sliced onion and peppers.
Combine and whip the remaining ingredients and pour over the vegetables.
Stir several times at intervals before serving.
This recipe is best made a day previous to serving.

title: champagne punch
directions: Put block of ice in punch bowl.
Mix ingredients.
Add sherbet and fruit if desired.
Put ginger ale and champagne in just before serving.
Serve and enjoy.

title: lo-fat cinnamon orange biscotti(ideal for kitchenaid-type mixer; adapted from "bon appetit")
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare baking sheet with baking spray and flour.
Blend dry ingredients in bowl and set aside.
Beat sugar and butter in large bowl until blended; add eggs, one at a time until combined, thereafter the peel and vanilla.
Gently add dry ingredients to butter mixture; after combined add raisins. Divide dough in half, shaping two logs on the prepared baking sheet, about 3 inches wide and 3/4 inch high.
Bake 35 minutes or until firm to the touch.
Remove from oven and cook 5 minutes. Transfer logs onto cutting board and slice diagonally into 1/2 inch slices.
Arrange cut side down on baking sheet and bake until bottoms are golden, about 10 minutes.
Turn over and repeat. Transfer to racks and cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: crepes with all fruit
directions: Use French whip to mix first 4 ingredients one at a time in order.
Spray large heated Teflon skillet with Pam spray.
Add 2/3 cup batter and rotate skillet to let batter run evenly over skillet bottom.
Turn crepe over after batter is no longer shiny. If difficult to turn, add 1 tablespoon flour to the batter and try again.
If any problems on second try, use 1/3 cup of batter and try again.
Serve hot spread with 2 teaspoons raspberry All Fruit and roll up.
If desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook stew beef until tender.
Cool and trim excess fat.
Put apart.
Drain.
Add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, vinegar, onions and Texas Pete.
Mix up and cook 3 to 4 hours. Add water if it gets too thick.
Use for sandwiches.

title: bean bowl salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients and put all in a big jar and keep refrigerated.

title: shake and bake mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in airtight container.
Use for chicken and chops.
Will last 6 weeks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all items together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish (pan) at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix together.
Spoon in scoops of sherbet (any flavor).
Most punch bowls will hold a double batch.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients except yeast.
Sprinkle yeast in mixture last. Work up like you do biscuits.
Roll out the amount you need and cut as biscuits.
Bake at 450°.
Place remaining dough in tightly closed large bowl (dough will continue to to rise).
Place in refrigerator and pinch off amount of dough needed when you want more biscuits.
Biscuits do not need to rise before baking, will rise as they bake.

title: fruit ice drink
directions: Boil sugar and water until it makes a thin syrup.
Cool.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill 1 hour in refrigerator. Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown and drain the first 3 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients, undrained. Cook for 30 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine flour and seasoning in plastic bag.
Put cut up chicken in the bag and shake to coat with flour.
Put oil in heavy skillet and put oil in heavy skillet and put chicken in.
Bake about 30 minutes on each side at 450°.

title: pecan pie brownies
directions: Remove 2/3 cup yellow cake mix from box.
Combine remaining cake mix with 1 egg and 1/2 cup butter/margarine.
Mix until it becomes a dough.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg, then sour milk, flour, salt, soda and rhubarb.
Mix well and pour into an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: freezer sweet pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand in refrigerator 2 hours. Drain well and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well a few times. Pack in container and freeze.

title: paprika chicken
directions: In skillet, combine soup, paprika and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat for 5 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring often.

title: crab canapes
directions: Mash well the cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise, crabmeat, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: crabby mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss crabmeat with lemon juice.
Add next five ingredients and mix well.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Rinse baking sheet lightly with water, shaking off excess.
Arrange mushrooms on sheet.
Cover with foil and bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking until tops are golden, about 5 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°; mix well shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Place 1/2 teaspoon date filling on dough and cover with 1/2 teaspoon dough. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed sole
directions: Saute onion, shrimp and mushrooms in butter until onion is tender.
Add crabmeat and heat through.
Sprinkle fillets with salt, pepper and paprika.
Spoon crabmeat mixture on fillets.
Roll up and fasten with toothpick.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, broth and water.
Blend until smooth. Pour over fillets.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Return to oven uncovered for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yields 8 servings.

title: easy mexicorn cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and stir well.
Mix milk, beaten eggs and vegetable oil together.
Add dry ingredients and milk mixture together with Mexicorn and mix.
Stir in cheese.
Add onion.
Make sure mixture is stirred together.
Pour in hot greased skillet. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Place all ingredients, except apples and nuts, in mixing bowl. Beat with spoon until mixed well. Add 1/2 cup nuts and apples. Pour mix in 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with remaining nuts. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar when cool.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Uncover and continue cooking until sauce is reduced to desired consistency.
Yields dinner for 4.

title: noodle bake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles, cheese mix and hamburger. Repeat layers.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine milk with sugar and salt in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add marshmallows, nuts, chocolate bits and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat butter and water in a saucepan to boiling point.
Stir in the flour all at once.
Stir vigorously, over low heat, until mixture leaves the pan and forms into a ball (about 1 minute). Remove from heat.
Beat in one egg at a time.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes; rinse under running cold water.
Grate potatoes and onion into a large bowl, half filled with cold water.
Line colander with clean towel or cheesecloth and pour potatoes and onion in to drain.
Squeeze potatoes and onions with towel to remove as much water as possible.
The drier the potatoes, the better the pancakes will be.

title: dill cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
This is a great dip for vegetables and if made with low-fat cottage cheese and mayonnaise, it is very healthy.

title: norwegian meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion and seasoning as for regular meatballs. Roll into small size meatballs (1-inch in diameter). Cook meatballs under broiler oven until done (approximately 2 to 3 minutes), turning.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl.
Beat eggs in small bowl until light.
Add to butter and sugar, beat well.
Add flour and soda, add mashed bananas.
Beat thoroughly.
Add nuts and water.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chalupas
directions: Puree Ro-Tel tomatoes in blender.
In separate pans, heat beans and Ro-Tel.
Fry tortillas in oil for 1 minute on each side until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towel and salt lightly.
Discard oil and brown meat.
Add cumin, salt and pepper.
Spread hot beans on each tortilla.
Over beans, sprinkle a layer each of meat, onion, lettuce and tomatoes.
Spoon over each hot Ro-Tel and top each with cheese.

title: meat loaf
directions: Cut vegetables into small pieces. Mix all ingredients and put into loaf pan to bake.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat and cook with bell pepper, tomatoes, onion, salt and pepper and chili powder. Then pour in uncooked rice and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Mix all together and heat.
Last 20 minutes of cooking chickens, brush on often.
This makes enough for at least 15 chickens.
Freeze all that is not used.

title: `the original buffalo' chicken wings
directions: Bake wings at 425° for 1 hour.
Combine red hot sauce and butter.
Dip wings in sauce to eat.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Grease two 9 x 6 or 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Heat in double boiler water, honey and cooking oil until warm.
Blend on low speed or by hand whole wheat flour, dry milk, salt, yeast and all-purpose flour.
Pour warm (not hot) liquid over flour mixture.
Knead on floured surface about 5 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise 45 to 60 minutes until light and double in bulk. Punch down dough and divide in half.
Shape each half into loaf by rolling dough into 14 x 7-inch rectangle.
Starting with 7-inch side, roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place in greased pan.
Cover loaves; let rise 40 to 45 minutes until light and doubled.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fresh cucumber delight
directions: Will also need a quart jar.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil and set aside to cool.
Wash, peel and slice cucumbers thick.
Place onion and garlic in jar.
Add cucumbers and fill to top.
Fill jar with vinegar mixture and close.
Refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
Always keep in refrigerator.
Will stay very crisp and may be used later.
Will keep for months.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix together the first 2
ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Batter will be stiff.

title: spaghetti with ricotta(ricotta con pasta)
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
While spaghetti is cooking, mix Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
When spaghetti
is
done "al dente" drain lightly and place in serving
platter.
Toss
with
butter
and
then Ricotta cheese mixture.
If a
little
dry, add a little water from cooking spaghetti.
Sprinkle
with
additional
Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lomi salmon
directions: Remove the skin from the salmon fillet and cut it into small squares.
Cut 3 lemons in half and squeeze the juice into a bowl. Remove all seeds, please.
Place the salmon squares in the lemon and add 1/2 cup white vinegar and a teaspoon of salt.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, salt, pepper, onions, cheese and butter in large bowl.
Add hash browns, stir.
Add bacon bits, mix and pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: gourmet cornbread
directions: Mix in order.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: celery casserole with almonds
directions: Remove outer stalks and leaves from celery.
Cut heads into quarters lengthwise; brown in butter.
Place in a shallow casserole with green peppers, parsley, chives, garlic and olive oil.
Top with almonds; pour on broth to a depth of 1/4 inch in casserole.
Cover; bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes, basting with liquid in casserole several times.
Uncover; baste again.
Cook until celery is tender.
Add more broth if needed during baking.
Serves 4.

title: carol's carrot and rice casserole
directions: Boil carrots and onion 10 minutes in as little water as possible.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into buttered casserole, dot with butter.
Place casserole in pan of hot water and bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve with chicken sauce: Use a can of cream of chicken soup and 1/2 to 2/3 cup milk and heat.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add milk, chicken broth, carrots, celery, dash of paprika and dash of salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Garnish with snipped parsley.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream the cheese and butter.
Add flour.
Mix well until mixture forms a ball.
Make 5 balls.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Place artichokes in greased casserole.
Combine spinach, 1/2 cup butter, cream cheese and lemon juice; pour over artichokes. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Prepare
cake mix as directed.
When cooled, split each layer to
form 4 layers in all.
Prepare filling of margarine, sugar and Crisco
by
mixing
for
7 minutes.
Add 5 to 6 oz. milk and beat another 7 minutes.
Place filling between layers and use prepared frosting on top layer and sides.
The cake is easier to frost if it is refrigerated for awhile after filling is placed between layers.

title: easy texas sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into ungreased 12 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine warm water, dry milk and sugar. Add 1 cup flour and beat hard 2 minutes. Add oil, egg whites and salt. Beat 3 minutes more. Add remaining flour and knead until elastic.
Put in greased bowl, turning twice to grease both sides. Cover and let rise double in bulk.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Add meat, mushrooms and bean curd. Simmer until meat is done.
Add soy sauce, sherry (7-Up), salt, pepper, vinegar, bamboo shoots and carrots and m.s.g.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Serve when thickened.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pancakes
directions: Blend egg, milk and oil.
Blend dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture.
Beat with rotary beater until all flour is moistened (batter will be slightly lumpy).
Spray frying pan with Pam.
Heat to medium high.
To test sprinkle drops of water in pan.
When water sizzles, heat is just right.
Pour 1 pancake at a time into skillet.
Turn pancakes as soon as they are puffed and full.
Turn and brown on other side.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and mix first 7 ingredients together.
Cover bottom of baking dish with chipped up corn tortillas.
Pour half mixture over and add another layer of chipped tortillas, then remaining chicken mixture.
Top with American cheese.
Bake until bubbly, about 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Heat jello and pineapple together.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water and cottage cheese.
Stir together.
Refrigerate.
Let it start to gel and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in Tupperware.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients and cover wings in an airtight container for at least 24 hours (refrigerated).
Bake for 1 hour or barbecue on grill.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Mix all of the above and bake in a sprayed Bundt pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 9-inch shallow unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: honey basted chicken
directions: Dip chicken into other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Baste with marinade.

title: fall spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine cake mix, water, eggs, oil and apple butter in bowl. Beat at low speed until blended, then medium speed for 2 minutes longer. Pour into prepared pans. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Cool completely. Spread Maple Buttercream Frosting all over cake and press nuts into sides of cake.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition.
Add flour and 7-Up and mix well.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: microwave caramel nut ring
directions: Melt oleo in glass pie plate; add water, brown sugar and nuts. Cut biscuits into quarters and coat with mixture; arrange around pan (may have to push together).
Place a cup in the center of pan.
Microwave at 70% for 4 minutes; turn onto a plate and cool 2 minutes if family will wait that long.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook rice. Blanch peppers about 20 minutes.
Brown onion and meat; put in peppers and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend butter and sugar until creamy. Beat in molasses. Sift flour. Resift with spices and baking soda and salt.
Add the sifted ingredients to the butter mixture in about 3 parts, alternately with either 1/4 cup water or 1/3 cup water

title: quick shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Combine butter and next 4 ingredients in large skillet; heat until bubbly.
Reduce heat to medium; add shrimp.
Cook, stirring frequently until shrimp turn pink (about 5 minutes).
Add parsley and hot sauce; toss lightly.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: homemade soft taco shells
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl (except 1/4 cup milk).
Mix with a wire whisk until well blended.
Spray a small 8-inch skillet with cooking spray.
Place skillet on medium heat.
Put 1/2 cup batter in pan and roll it around (it will stick to the sides of the pan). Flip it over when edges are brown.
Stir batter between each shell. As batter becomes thick, add the remaining 1/4 cup milk.

title: mexican potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes whole until done.
Cool and slice.
Layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add cheese and tomatoes.
Stir together until melted. Pour over potatoes and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients in plastic bag.
Melt margarine in cookie sheet with sides.
Shake 2 to 3 pieces of chicken at a time in plastic bag to coat with dry ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes and then turn chicken over and bake for another 20 minutes.

title: easy chip dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and chilies together.
Stir in salsa and Cheddar cheese.
Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: honey milk bars
directions: Heat honey and peanut butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
