Pat into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate and cut into bars.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Sift flour, measure and resift twice with baking powder and salt.
Cream the butter.
Blend in sugar thoroughly and add egg. Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Divide dough into 2 portions.
Stir cooled melted chocolate into one portion and chill both in refrigerator for 1/2 hour or longer.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend crumbs (crackers), Parmesan cheese, parsley and seasonings. Dip each chicken piece in melted butter, then in crumb mixture.
Arrange in casserole dish. Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake 1 hour.
Do not turn or cover.
Serves 8.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Toss apples with next 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Scoop apples into buttered pie pan.
Pat dough mixture onto apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamed ham on cornbread
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, combine margarine, flour, salt and dry mustard.
Stir in milk and soup.
Heat until bubbling.
Add cubed ham.
Pour over cornbread squares.
Serves 4.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together once the flour, soda and cinnamon.
Cream oil and sugar.
Add dry ingredients alternately with eggs, using one egg at a time.
Add vanilla.
Last, fold in grated carrots.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: crab chowder
directions: Lightly cook celery and onion.
Add as much crab as you are lucky enough to catch.
Heat all ingredients through; cover and let set 15 or 20 minutes.
You can use oysters and clams with or in place of crab.

title: fruit punch
directions: Use blender or food processor.
Makes 7 cups punch.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Add softened cream cheese, beating with mixer.
Stir in half of the whipped topping.

title: cheesy hash browns 'n ham
directions: Spread 1 teaspoon oleo on each side of hash browns.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn patties over; broil 4 to 6 minutes more.
Place ham slice on each patty.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coffee sponge cake(diabetic)
directions: Scald nonfat milk.
Dissolve coffee and 1/3 sugar substitute (equivalent to 1/4 cup sugar) in scalded milk; chill until slightly thickened.
Beat four egg whites stiff.
Fold in coffee mixture.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.
Beat remaining egg whites gradually, adding remaining sugar substitute.
Continue beating until stiff.
Spread over mold with spatula bringing to edges.

title: whitney's rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in
microwave for 3 to 4 minutes. Stir mixture well.
Add 1 cup peanut butter and stir.
Mix in 6 cups of Rice Krispies and mix well.
Spray hands and 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam and spread mixture into pan.
Press gently.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mixture will look curdled.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: nut cookies
directions: Mix together last 3 ingredients.
This is the mix you roll the dough out on.

title: hearty chicken noodle soup
directions: Stew chicken in broth until very tender.
Drain, reserving broth.
Bone chicken and flake into large, bite-size pieces. Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse.
Put a small amount of the broth into a saucepan and cook carrots, celery and onions until tender.
Add frozen peas. Add remaining chicken broth, cooked noodles and flaked chicken. Serve with crusty bread.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Mix melted butter, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Coat chicken pieces and place in foil-lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Cook chicken; remove bones and skin and cut into small pieces (save broth).
Make stuffing mix according to directions using chicken broth instead of water.
Mix chicken and stuffing together.
Mix 2 cans of soup with remaining chicken broth and pour over stuffed shells.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling into 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch baking pan; spread evenly.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over filling.
Cover dry cake mix with butter slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Blueberry pie filling may be used instead of cherry.
Serves 8.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon.
Put in baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Crumble bacon over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Can be baked in microwave.)

title: bread dressing casserole
directions: Brown celery and onion in margarine and set aside.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add celery mixture to hamburger.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with bread dressing.
Mix cans of soup and water.
Pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix soup and milk together.
Place pork chops in baking dish. Pour mixture over chops.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Add sliced cheese or grated cheese to top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: fig cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In medium bowl combine figs, sugar and flour; mix well. Spoon into an 8 inch square baking pan; dot with butter. Roll pastry into 1/4 inch thickness on lightly floured surface; cut into 9 -- 1/2 inch strips. Arrange strips in lattice pattern over fig mixture. Trim edges as needed. Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 6 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add flour and baking soda.
Then add sour cream and vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 325°, until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil; let cook about 3 minutes. Pour into baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients all together and pour over peach mixture.
Mix all together with spoon.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix with flour, cinnamon and sugar.
Add beaten egg and apples.
Pour into crust. Cook at 375° for 10 minutes, then at 350° until done. Takes about 1 hour or longer.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Butter rectangle pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Heat corn syrup, butter and chocolate chips to boiling in saucepan, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large bowl; toss quickly until completely coated with chocolate.
Add marshmallows, 1 cup at a time.
Press mixture evenly in pan.
Let stand until firm, cut into squares.

title: korean buffet
directions: Brown ground beef in oil in skillet, stirring until crumbly. Add remaining ingredients. Cook until vegetables are tender and crisp. Stir constantly. Serve over egg noodles with soy sauce. Yields 6 servings.

title: lil' pecan pies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soft margarine and sugar.
Then add flour.
Beat eggs and add in.
Add Karo syrup and vanilla.
Then add pecans last.
Place all 16 pie tarts on a large cookie sheet. Spoon out evenly into 16 pie tarts the pecan pie mixture.
Each pie tart will be about 3/4 full.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes. If oven cooks hotter, it may take less time to cook.
Make sure crusts on tarts are brown and inside of tart doesn't shake when you take them out of the oven.

title: pecan sandies(cookies)
directions: Cream the butter and sugars. Add egg. Add dry ingredients. Stir in nuts. Bake at 350° until light brown on edges, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked spareribs "aloha"
directions: Put ribs in a roasting pan.
Salt and pepper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Drain off fat.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes longer. Baste frequently with sauce.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer olives, tomato, cauliflower, broccoli, Cheddar cheese and lettuce.
Put Miracle Whip, sugar and Parmesan cheese on top. Before serving, stir up.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together all ingredients except bacon.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with bacon.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in an 8-inch square greased baking pan.

title: apple dumpling cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients into a large bowl. Mix with your hands as you would a meat loaf, gently but thoroughly.
Do not use a spoon or mixer.
Bake in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan or Bundt pan for about an hour.

title: ruth's pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour with pastry blender.
Add other ingredients.
Form in balls of dough.
Roll out for pie pans.

title: fluffy fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients except bananas.
Let set overnight.
Add bananas before serving.

title: layered peach dessert
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in order.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla in a bowl until light and fluffy.
Work in dry ingredients (flour) until mixture is smooth. Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.

title: aunt deb's brown paper bag apple pie
directions: You will need 1 brown paper bag.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour.
Combine baking soda and sour cream; add eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup water; add vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Combine all, mixing well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Frost with 7-Minute Frosting. Makes either a 2 layer cake or a sheet cake.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Combine and heat, but do not boil, the first 4 ingredients. After sugar dissolves, cool.
Add the heavy cream and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Store in covered jar.
Will keep for months.
Serve over ice cream or favorite puddings.

title: susan's poppy seed chicken
directions: Spray casserole with Pam.
Place diced chicken in casserole. Mix soup and sour cream and pour over top.
Crush crackers and mix in poppy seed.
Sprinkle over top.
Pour melted butter over all. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven, uncovered.

title: boiled custard
directions: Heat milk over very low heat. Mix flour and sugar. Add to hot milk. Beat eggs. Add a little hot milk to the beaten eggs. Then add eggs to the milk mixture. Stir constantly. It's ready when it coats a metal spoon. Mixture will thicken as it cools.

title: chocolate upside-down pudding
directions: Melt chocolate in oleo.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, milk and vanilla.
Mix sugar and brown sugar with cocoa.
Spread on top of the batter.
Pour water over each pan.
Don't grease pan.

title: marsha's spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Serve with Sociable crackers.

title: lemon icebox cake
directions: Beat egg yolks; add lemon juice, extract or lemon rind and beat well.
Add one can of milk and mix thoroughly.
Crumble a dozen or so vanilla wafers and press them into bottom of pie pan. Add about 12 to 14 whole wafers around edge of pie pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Beat egg whites.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar. Spread this mixture over pie and brown in oven.
Cool and chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugars, flour and salt in bowl.
Blend well.
Stir in eggs and milk, but do not beat.
Add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Stir to mix well and then turn into 8-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl. Pour into 2 pie shells. Bake at 375° from 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: oriental hash
directions: Brown meat, celery and onion.
Drain liquid.
Add soy sauce. Add soups and rice; mix well. Put in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: lemon gooey
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg. Pat well into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese; cream in milk. Blend in lemon juice and vanilla. Chill and top with pie filling and fruit.

title: 30 minute stew
directions: Cover potatoes and carrots with water.
Add onion and black pepper.
Cook until carrots and potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add beef with gravy and bouillon.
Heat through.
Thicken with cornstarch mixed with a little water.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: beanie weenies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in a microwavable dish.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes. Serves 4.

title: spinach rockafeller
directions: Combine all ingredients together and bake in 2-quart dish. Top with Parmesan liberally. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: fred's favorite dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until almost brown (about 20 minutes).

title: raisin pumpkin cake
directions: Bake in a large Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: party casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Make white sauce with butter, flour, milk and salt.
Cook until medium thick.
Cut cooked broccoli into 1-inch pieces and place in buttered casserole.
Combine ham, green pepper, parsley, eggs, cheese and lemon juice.
Place over broccoli.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom of oblong baking dish. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Chill.
Cream together the cheese, milk and sugar. Spread on crust.
Sprinkle layer of nuts over cheese.
Whip the cream stiffly and add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spread over nuts in a layer.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Spread all of the cherry pie filling over the cream.
Let chill overnight. Cut into squares and lift out with spatula.

title: friendship cake
directions: Add these ingredients to your portion of remaining batter.

title: pork chops and kraut
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops. Brown in a small amount of oil. Pour off excess fat.
Put a spoonful of kraut on top of each chop.
Place potato chunks around meat and add 1/2 cup water. Cover and cook on low heat approximately 1 hour or until pork chops are tender.
Extra liquid may be added, if needed.

title: chicken rice dressing
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Melt oleo in oven pan and add pepper, onion, and seasoning.
Add rice.
Mix soups with water.
Slowly pour over rice.
Decorate top with pimentos. Cook in oven for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well, serve with sugar cookies or gingersnaps.

title: low-fat graham honey rolls
directions: Combine 1 cup bread flour and next 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl, stirring well.
Combine water, honey and margarine in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until margarine melts, stirring occasionally.
Cool to 120°.
Gradually add liquid mixture to flour mixture, beating well at low speed of mixer.
Beat an additional 2 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually stir in graham flour and enough of the remaining 2 cups bread flour to make a soft dough.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 tablespoons bread flour evenly over work surface.
Turn dough out onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Place dough in a large bowl coated with cooking spray, turning to coat top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (95°) free from drafts, 45 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down and divide into 32 equal portions.
Roll each portion into a 9-inch rope.
Tie each rope in a loose knot, leaving 2 long ends.
Place on large baking sheets coated with cooking spray. Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, 30 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 13 minutes or until golden.
Coat rolls lightly with cooking spray.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grate carrots into large bowl.
Add oil and mix.
Then add and mix sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Measure, add and mix in the flour, soda and salt.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
When cool, spread with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: macaroni and cheese delight
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Loosen edges and invert onto serving platter.

title: grandma aligood's banana-nut bread
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Stir in shortening.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add bananas and nuts.
Grease well a loaf pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: nut bread
directions: Beat
2 eggs with 2 cups milk, stir in the dry ingredients, put in two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Heat 7-Up and pour over jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Mix cream cheese with hot water until smooth.
Add cream cheese mixture and remaining ingredients together.
Pour into a refrigerator bowl and chill several hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: venison roast
directions: Season roast with garlic salt, salt and pepper and onion. Wrap roast completely with bacon and hold bacon in place with toothpicks.

title: s'mores pie
directions: Mix ice cream, marshmallows and Hershey bars; pour into pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Top with additional chopped Hershey bars.

title: sourdough waffles or pancakes
directions: Eighteen hours before you wish to serve the pancakes or at least the night before, measure 1 cup Starter, 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup of milk in nonmetal bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Let stand at 80° to 85° until morning.
I put mine on top of fridge.

title: herring salad
directions: Drain herring; cut into small pieces.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in casserole dish.

title: christmas sugar cookie
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk and vanilla, then dry ingredients. Chill dough before rolling and cutting in desired shapes.
Dough can also be frozen for later use.
Bake cookies at 400° for 7 minutes.
These cookies are not only delicious but very pretty since the dough is very white.
They can be decorated with icing for the holidays.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well. Brown crumbs in melted margarine.
Mix onion soup mix, sour cream and 1 cup cheese with spinach.

title: lemon lush layers
directions: Combine flour and 1 cup walnuts.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing until well blended.
Fold in 1 container of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding mix using 3 cups milk. Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding layer.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 cup of cracker crumbs.
Put in casserole dish and top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: canned unshelled raw peanuts
directions: You will need quart jars, lids and bands and a pressure canner.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Blend well. Sprinkle coconut into pastry shell.
Pour egg mixture over coconut. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool; garnish with whipped cream.
Yield:
One 9-inch pie.

title: garlic and herb rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a baking sheet.
In a large bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt, thyme, baking soda and pepper.
Add buttermilk or yogurt, scallions and oil.
Stir until a soft dough forms.
Drop by scant 1/4 cupfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for about 12 minutes.

title: ultimate bran muffins
directions: Combine bran, flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder in mixing bowl.
Beat egg, brown sugar, oil, buttermilk, molasses, raisins and apricots together thoroughly.
Add liquid ingredients all at once; stir, then add dry ingredients.
Stir until just moistened.
Fill paper lined muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 23 minutes in 375° oven.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: cherry bran muffins
directions: Mix together bran cereal, milk, brown sugar, eggs and oil. Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients except cherry pie filling.
Add bran mixture all at once and stir only until moistened.
Fill greased muffin tins.
Make an indentation in the mixture by placing a spoon of pie filling with 2 to 3 cherries in the center of each muffin.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in preheated 400° oven.

title: strawberry and pineapple jam for freezer
directions: Wash, scald and drain jelly glasses and tight fitting lids. Wash, hull and crush strawberries in a large bowl.
Drain pineapple juice into a measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Reserve.
Add pineapple and sugar to strawberries. Stir and let stand 10 minutes.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt; stir in mixture.
Stir and mix in pecans, cherries and dates.
Mix all together and chill.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop by teaspoonful 2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Top with pecan half or half candied cherries.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple pudding *
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, juice and boiling water.
Cook until thick.
Add egg yolks and butter.
Put a layer of vanilla wafers into dish, then a layer of pineapple, then sauce.
Repeat layers in this order.
Whipped cream can be used instead of meringue.

title: best ever cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, green pepper, onion, seasoned salt, pineapple and 2 1/2 cups nuts together with hands.
Form mixture into a ball.
Roll in remaining nuts until completely covered. Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake in greased pan at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves of bread.

title: nut goody bars
directions: Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips in a double boiler over hot water.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Remove from heat.
Add walnuts and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into an 8-inch square pan.
Cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen bars.

title: toffee truffle
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package; cool.
Prepare instant pudding as indicated on package.
Remove candy bars (which have been frozen) from the freezer.
Break
up candy bars with a mallet.
Break apart cooled cake.

title: chinese chicken and cabbage salad
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces; add cabbage, sesame seed, almonds and green onions.
Shake together sugar, oil, salt, Accent, pepper and vinegar.
Add to salad.
Add crunched up noodles right before serving.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices into creamed mixture.
Mix.
Shape size of walnuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten a little with fork dipped in flour and can sprinkle with sugar if you want. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple with dry pudding mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients. In bottom of baking pan, place 1 cup ketchup. Place meat mixture on top and shape to form meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wilson's family special
directions: In bowl, stir together the mushroom soup, milk, dry onion soup mix and undrained mushrooms.
Reserve 3/4 cup of the soup mixture and set aside.
Stir in uncooked rice and thawed vegetables into remaining soup mixture.
Turn rice mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken pieces atop.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° until rice is tender, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: canned razor clam dip
directions: Chop razor clams and use some of the juice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Store in fridge several hours before serving.

title: cola cake
directions: Bring oil, margarine and Coke to boil.
Add marshmallows and cool.
Add all dry ingredients to marshmallow mixture.
Bake in well-greased pan (9 1/2 x 11-inch) at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: heloise's mom's meringue pie shells
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and dry (cannot overbeat).
Slowly add sugar to stiff egg whites.
Slowly add vanilla and vinegar to egg whites, beat until stiff.
Use back of ungreased aluminum cookie sheet.
Plop six great globs of egg white.
Don't put too close together.
They grow to twice their size.
Make little wells with back of spoon on each in the center.
Bake in middle shelf at 250° for an hour or until pinkish beige in color.
The tips do not get dark.
Before taking out of oven touch bottom of each well to be sure it isn't sticky.
Immediately place on wax paper or dessert plates or they will break.
Fill with fruit and top with whipped cream.
Can be made like small cookies.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In large container, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, spoon 3 heaping tablespoons of mix into mug.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Garnish if desired.

title: stuffed venison loin
directions: Take one venison or cantaloupe loin and cut lengthwise part way through.
Stuff with diced onions, green peppers and mushrooms. Wrap with bacon.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Wrap with aluminum foil and barbecue until done.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick vegetable spray.
Mix together pecans and coconut and spread on bottom of the pan.
Set aside.
Prepare cake mix batter according to package directions.
Pour over pecans and coconut mixture.
In a mixing bowl, cream together the cream cheese, margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls over batter. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash berries and drain well.
Peel and seed orange.
Combine orange and berries in food processor or blender.
Blend well.
Add sugar and refrigerate.
This is best if made a day ahead of time.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with electric mixer.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Microwave at Medium-high (70%) until cheese melts, 6 1/2 to 8 minutes, stirring to blend well once or twice, during cooking.
Serve with corn chips or snack crackers, if desired.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: *Cream of mushroom soup may be substituted for celery soup.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, eggs and milk; add flour, baking powder and salt.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Pour salad dressing into baking dish; add chicken and coat. Cover to chill 4 hours.
Drain, reserving dressing.
Dip chicken in egg and water and then into combination of dry ingredients. Return chicken to baking dish, pouring remaining dressing on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poor man's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg.
Saute garlic, parsley and onions.
Then add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 2 hours.

title: apricot and pineapple smoothie
directions: In a blender, combine 2 cups of the apricot nectar, one third of the pineapple chunks, one third of the dates, 1 cup of ice cubes and 1/2 tablespoon of the bee pollen.
If using:
blend until smooth.
Pour into 2 chilled glasses.
Make 2 more batches in the same fashion.
Makes 9 cups - serves 6.

title: tomato-kraut bake
directions: Can of kraut and tomatoes should be same size and drained well.
Recipe based on 16 ounce size.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix chicken, cream cheese and onion together. Add garlic salt, parsley and Worcestershire to taste. Form into a ball, roll in chopped almonds.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use cracker crumb crust or cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until top is bubbling.

title: oriental marinade
directions: Mix and pour over chicken, beef or pork.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine
meat, rice, salt and pepper.
Shape into small balls. Combine
onion, bell pepper and tomato soup.
Pour all ingredients into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: marinated vidalias
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Combine water, sugar and vinegar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over onion rings. Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Drain.
Stir in mayo and celery seed.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: apricot whip
directions: Heat the pineapple and sugar.
Stir in Jell-O.
Let cool until thickens.
Blend the cream cheese, milk and Cool Whip; mix all together.

title: tomato soup
directions: Saute onions in butter in 4-quart soup pot until transparent. Add garlic and cook 1 minute.
Add stock; bring to a boil and add rice.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Peel and dice tomatoes and add to pot along with tomato juice and chopped basil.
Cook over low heat another 15 minutes.
Add salt to taste.
Serves 6.

title: mama's chow chow
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cook 1 1/2 hours or until thick.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly in large bowl, stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Stir into egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts by hand.
Put into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake until center springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pans or on wire rack 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves, pan sizes 8 x 5 x 3-inch pans.

title: eva st.  clair's corn custard pudding
directions: Cook corn according to directions on package.
Melt butter or margarine.
Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: donna's ginger cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and mix into remaining ingredients.
Form into small balls (size of hickory nuts).
Roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 25 minutes.

title: super beefy enchiladas
directions: Combine beef, 1/2 of cheese and onion. Cook until cheese is melted. Set aside. Combine soups and enchilada sauce. Cook and set aside. Dip tortillas into hot oil to soften. Top each tortilla with meat mixture. Roll up. Place seam side down in 13 x 9 pan. Pour sauce over the top. Sprinkle remaining grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix and pour over chicken the Veg-All, soups and chicken broth. Mix and pour over mixture in casserole the flour and buttermilk. This mixture needs to be pourable. Melt oleo and drizzle over biscuit mixture. Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: nutty peach crisp(12 to 15 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer all ingredients in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes, or until top is golden brown.
Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm or cool and, if desired, with sweetened whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pancakes
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well. Heat griddle until drops of water sizzle. Cook until bubbles form on surface.

title: garlic chicken fillets in balsamic vinegar
directions: Split chicken breasts in half lengthwise and dredge in flour; remove excess.
In a large, heavy skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Cook chicken on one side, about 2 to 3 minutes, or until golden.
Add garlic.
Turn chicken and continue cooking, about 2 to 3 minutes, or until golden.
Add stock, balsamic vinegar and pepper.
Reduce heat.
Cover skillet and cook 5 to 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Keep warm.

title: peppernoetter(peppernuts)
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Stir in the cream.
Sift in the flour and baking soda. Stir well.
(It may be a little hard to stir; you might want to work in with your hands.)
Sift together the cinnamon, cardamom and pepper.
Add and stir well. Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies will flatten out a little, but they will still be rounded and plump.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and arrange on nonstick pizza pan to form one large cookie.
Wet fingers and press cookie slices together to form one solid cookie.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Before cookie cools completely, loosen from pan with knife or spatula.

title: green tomato relish(sweet)
directions: Using food processor, chop green peppers, red peppers, onions, cabbage, green tomatoes and sugar until they yield amounts in parentheses.
Mix chopped vegetables well and soak overnight in water with 1/2 cup pickling salt added.
Rinse well in cold water and drain.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg together.
Stir in milk and bananas.
In a separate bowl sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well with banana mixture.
Blend in nuts.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 70 minutes or until pick stuck in center comes out clean (crack down center is characteristic).

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Slice carrots 1/4-inch thick and cook in boiling water until barely done; drain.
Add onions and peppers.
Mix other ingredients to make dressing.
Pour over carrots and refrigerate overnight.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Bring 1 inch of water to boil in a pan; add onions and potatoes and 2 teaspoons salt. Boil for 5 minutes, drain. Melt butter in saucepan, blend in flour, pepper and remaining teaspoon of salt. Add milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Combine potatoes and onions with cream sauce. Place in a shallow baking dish and sprinkle cheese on top, if desired. Bake, uncovered, at 400 ° for 35 minutes or until golden and bubbly. Serves 4 to 5.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add eggs and milk.
Cook until thick. Remove from stove.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into Crisco pie shell which has already been cooked.
Make meringue with egg whites.
Brown meringue in a 400° oven until nice and brown.

title: fiesta rice
directions: Combine onion, garlic and
oil
in 2 quart glass casserole. Cover.
Microwave on High 2
to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients;
cover.
Microwave
on
High 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Microwave on
Medium
12 to 15 minutes until rice is tender and liquid
is
absorbed.
Let stand 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork.

title: white potato casserole
directions: Mix onion, bell pepper, salt, pepper and butter in a pot. Pour in a small amount of water.
Boil until almost done.
Remove from heat to cool.
Then put in flour, milk and eggs.
Beat well. Place potatoes in a deep casserole dish.
Pour in mixture. Scatter cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 35 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: spice cake and penuche frosting
directions: Bake and cool according to directions on box.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Sift flour and spices together.
Add soda and buttermilk, then raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in moderate oven about 325° until done in 2 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Mix yeast, 1/2 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 cup water and let stand. Mix 1 1/2 cups water and egg. Mix flour and salt. Mix Crisco and 1/2 cup sugar. Add egg water to melted shortening mixture and add yeast mixture. Pour this over top of flour mixture. Knead well or do in mixer with dough hook until sides of bowl clean. Place in oil sprayed bowl and cover with Saran or Saran quick covers. Let rise 1/2 to 1 hour. Punch down. Divide into 32 pieces. Roll each piece flat and place 2 pepperoni slices and 1 to 2 cubes cheese. Shape into roll. Bake on ungreased or parchment lined cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°. Brush tops with butter while hot.

title: salmon patties
directions: *Add milk to liquid to make 3/4 cup.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars over low heat, stirring. Remove from heat. Fold in very cold whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.

title: mom's 3-cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large greased casserole, place a layer of potatoes, then of onions, then some of each of the cheeses.
Season well with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers until ingredients are used up. Pour bouillon over the top.
Sprinkle on some reserved Parmesan. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until the potatoes are very tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then stir in cabbage and mix all together. Chill and serve.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; work in flour until well mixed. Press into well-greased 8 or 9-inch cake pan.
Prick with fork. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares; remove from pan when slightly cooled.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Boil hamburg with just enough water to cover.
When no longer pink, add diced potatoes and onions.
Cook, covered, on low heat until potatoes are tender. Mix flour and eggs; drop by spoonful into mixture.
Cover; cook on medium for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: gouda wellington
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Using fingers press perforations on dough to seal and form a solid rectangle.
Remove casing from cheese and place in center of sough.
Cover cheese with preserves. Fold dough around cheese.
Brush top with beaten egg white.
Bake in a 350 degree preheated oven for 30 minutes, or until brown. Garnish with sesame seeds.
Allow to set and cut into wedges and serve.

title: seven layer dip
directions: In serving dish, layer the ingredients in the order given. Chill and serve for dip!

title: cheesy round steak
directions: Cut steak into pieces; pour to 1/2-inch thick.
Combine egg to milk and crumbs with salt and pepper.
Dip steak into egg bath, then into bread crumbs.
Brown meat in drippings.
Add water; sprinkle on oregano.
Place 2 tablespoons of cheese on each piece. Put onions on meat.
Cover and cook at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: You will need 1-quart casserole dish with lid or use foil for top.

title: party mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Melt almond bark in microwave or double boiler.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix until well coated.
Pour out onto wax paper and let set.
Break apart into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips and margarine with condensed milk and vanilla; remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine marshmallows and pecans if desired; stir in chocolate mixture.
Spread in aluminum foil-lined 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Chill for 2 hours until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off foil and cut into squares.

title: carrots and raisins in wine
directions: In large skillet melt margarine.
Add wine and sugar; simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add carrots and stir to coat.
Cover; cook over high heat about 10 to 12 minutes or until tender-crisp and liquid is almost absorbed.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and pepper.
Stir in raisins.
Serves 4.

title: corn dumplings
directions: Combine baking mix, cornmeal and parsley.
Add milk and corn, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto your favorite simmering chili.
Cook uncovered over low heat for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer or until dumplings are dry.

title: golden cheesies(servings:  30)
directions: Have butter at room temperature.
Combine with sour cream in mixer; add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Mix well.
Divide mixture into 4 equal parts.
Wrap each chunk with waxed paper and refrigerate until firm.
Roll out one chunk at a time on floured board to 15 x 6-inch rectangle.
Salt and pepper and sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese.
Roll rectangle into 15-inch roll and seal ends and pull edge along top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place on foil or Saran Wrap to refrigerate or freeze until use.
Can go from freezer to cookie sheet to oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly and brown.
Slice in 1/2-inch pieces.

title: fish with mustard marinade
directions: Combine seasonings in a plastic bag and mix.
Add fillets and marinate for about 4 hours.
Drain fillets, dredge in cornmeal and deep fry in hot oil until browned.

title: texas baked beans
directions: Brown the ground round with onion, salt and pepper; drain fat off.
Add beans, brown sugar, chili sauce and mustard.
Stir into a buttered dish, cover.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Sprinkle seasoning salt on the chicken breasts.
Pour the French dressing over.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 375° to 400°.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute celery, onion, green pepper and garlic in butter.
Boil noodles in chicken broth.
Mix soup, Ro-Tel and cheese until melted.
Mix all ingredients.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla (or maple flavoring).
Add coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 greased 8-inch pans at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
When cool, frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: chocolate chip-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
together shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and
vanilla.
Sift and add remaining ingredients.	Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 8 to 9 dozen.

title: deviled crab
directions: Melt butter.
Saute bell pepper, celery and onion until done. Remove
from heat.
Let cool until warm.
Add all other ingredients.
Spoon into crab shells or aluminum shells or can be made into patties.
Top with extra bread crumbs and paprika. Brown in oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Blend apples with sugar and spices.
Add beaten egg, butter and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients; stir until well mixed.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry mash
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated milk, marshmallows and margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Boil 5 minutes and add cherry chips and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and add peanut butter and crushed peanuts.
Spread over cooled cherry layer.
Chill.

title: green stuff salad
directions: Mix pineapple (with juice) and pudding mix together.
Add cottage cheese and nuts.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: garlic-sauteed broccoli
directions: Remove 1/2 inch from bottom of broccoli robe stems.
Cut crosswise in 1-inch pieces, about 14 loosely packed cups.
Heat oil in large deep nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Stir in garlic and cook until aroma is released, 30 seconds to 1 minute, stirring once or twice.
(Don't let garlic color.)
Stir in salt and add broccoli.
Cover and cook 6 to 7 minutes, stirring and occasionally until leaves are just wilted and stems are crisp-tender.
Cook two more minutes until water is almost evaporated.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bring water to a boil; add soup mix and butter.
Stir to dissolve, and simmer a few minutes.

title: frosty mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges, measuring syrup; add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add measured liquid.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in oranges.
Pour into a serving bowl or individual serving dishes.
Chill until set, at least 1 hour. Makes about 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cheese. Add pineapple.
Mix well. Top with crumbs. Dot with butter or margarine. Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes then reduce oven to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Beat with electric mixer the mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasoning mix.
Add parsley, Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Serve with carrots, celery and cauliflower.

title: party casserole
directions: Cook onion, peppers and garlic in butter until clear.
Add mushrooms and soup, cheeses and olives.
Stir until cheese melts. Cook fettucini until almost done; drain.
Add sauce and mix.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: snow cone
directions: Take a cup of snow, add instant jello to desired taste. Enjoy!!!!

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine ingredients well, adding milk last to prevent lumping. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion;
drain.
Add mushrooms and soup. Simmer
minutes.
Add
sour
cream and cook 5 or 10 minutes more.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: summer fruit smoothie
directions: Blend all ingredients except ice cubes in a blender. Cover and blend until smooth. Add ice cubes; blend until thickened. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings, 3/4 cup each.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Rinse canned fish in sieve and drain.
Mix all ingredients and place in well-greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350°, until well heated, 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fresh fruit dessert
directions: Put pineapple and orange juice in pan and heat until boiling. Add vanilla pudding mix.
Stir well until thick.
Cool.

title: chocolate square oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add sugars, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in oats and pecans.
Shape dough into one 12-inch roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Slice and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated moderate 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and place small square of milk chocolate bar on each.
Remove from cookie sheet and press pecan halves onto melted chocolate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and save 1 cup of broth.
Tear chicken from bones.
Melt butter and mix with dressing.
Combine soups and broth.
Layer dressing, chicken and soups alternately.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Add your cooked and mashed sweet potatoes to your batter.
Fold in.
Do not overmix. Roll out on floured board and make your biscuits.
Bake in hot oven until done at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut open biscuits and add butter and brown sugar.
Can use your own biscuit recipe.

title: cheese quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 8 fajita-style tortillas on a baking sheet.
Top each tortilla evenly with 1/4 cup shredded cheese and sprinkle over with diced chilies.
Place in oven for 5 minutes or until the cheese melts.
Take out and fold each tortilla in half, then cut into 4 triangles.
Serve with salsa and sour cream when hot.

title: herb bubble ring
directions: Grease tube cake pan.
Mix first 5 ingredients; reserve.
Mix baking mix, sour cream and milk until a soft dough forms.
Smooth into ball on a floured board.
Knead 10 times.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip into margarine; roll in cheese mixture.
Arrange in layers in pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes so it will be easy to remove from pan.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Generously butter pan.
In mixing bowl, cream together butter and 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla and lemon juice.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add the creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, ending with dry ingredients.
In small mixing bowl, blend brown sugar, 1 tablespoon sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour half the batter into scalloped 7-cup tube pan or 10-inch tube pan and sprinkle brown-sugar mixture over batter.
Pour in remainder of batter. Bake 45 to 50 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: james' peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, karo, and water.
Cook until thread.
Add butter and peanuts.
Cook until syrup turns brown and peanuts are done.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda.
Mix well and pour onto aluminum foil.
Let cool, then snack.

title: katie's cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower flowerets into medium-sized pieces. Boil in salted water until tender; fork should slide out easily when tested. Drain and set aside.

title: baked beans with sausage
directions: Cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Brown sausages.
Mix all this with brown sugar, dry mustard, tomato paste and tomato soup.
Pour all this over beans.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Stir once in a while.

title: grape wine(old recipe, fun to make)
directions: Dissolve ingredients in warm water.
Pour into gallon jug; finish filling with water.
Place large balloon on mouth of jug; it will blow up as fermentation takes place.
Be careful that balloon doesn't burst.
Takes about 3 weeks.

title: stuffed cornish hen
directions: Place the fat in the skillet.
Fry onion and celery until tender. Add water and stuffing mix until stuffing is moist, but not soggy.
Stuff the cavity of each Cornish hen.
Place in baking bag or wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and brown lightly. Serve immediately.

title: baked rice
directions: Cook butter, onion and rice in skillet until onion is tender. Dissolve bouillon in water.
Add rice mixture and mushrooms and pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Ahead of time, cut 1/2 gallon sherbet into three sections and freeze separately.
Freeze some ginger ale in a mold to create a solid ice ring to float in punch.
(This keeps punch from being watered down from a regular ice ring.)

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Put sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Corn Flakes.
Stir.
Spoon on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: walnut spice cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and reserved liquid. Add vanilla and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Drop from teaspoon about
1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in moderate oven at 375°
about 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost while warm if desired.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream.
In a 2 1/2-quart round glass serving bowl, layer pudding, vanilla wafers and bananas. Chill thoroughly. Garnish as desired.

title: sweet peach pickles
directions: Peel peaches and stick with cloves.
Mix vinegar and sugar and bring to a boil.
Drop in peaches.
Let boil until tender.
Put in cans and seal while hot.

title: instant pudding fruit salad
directions: Wash strawberries and cut in half or fourths.
Slice bananas and toss in lemon juice.
Sprinkle pudding mix over strawberries and banana mixture.
Add peaches and juice.
Mix well and chill.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Let cool and add celery, onion and pepper.
Fry bacon until crisp.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; mix into creamed mixture at low speed until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts with a spoon.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies and 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies. Makes 3 dozen.

title: hillbilly beans
directions: Brown sausage or ground chuck with onion in skillet; drain. In large casserole or small roaster, mix together remaining ingredients.
Mix drained browned meat and onion with all other ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes a great picnic dish.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Mix cheese, bread and flour.
Add cooked, drained sausage. Place mixture in large greased casserole dish.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Pour egg mixture over ingredients in casserole.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set in the middle.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: percolator wassail
directions: *Finish filling with water to make 30 cups.

title: spinach balls hors d'oeuvres
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain (squeeze) spinach.
Mix margarine with spinach until melted.
Add cheese and eggs when spinach is cool.
Form into balls (1 tablespoon size).
Bake on cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 75 balls.
Can be frozen until needed.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook sirloin roast in crock-pot on low setting for 8 hours. Remove roast.
Allow broth to cool.
Remove grease from top of broth.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Chop onions and carrots.
Cover potatoes, onions and carrots with enough water to cook in a large stock pot.
Cook until tender.
Add beef broth, tomatoes, Veg-All and cubed roast beef.
Salt and pepper to taste.
The longer the soup simmers, the better the flavor.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Dough will be stiff.
Drop by spoon into tea cake pan.
Makes 24 biscuits in a tea pan or 12 in a cup cake pan. I prefer the tea cake size.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: neiman marcus brownies
directions: Mix above ingredients well and pat into a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: On a paper towel, mix first 7 ingredients.
In a mixing bowl, mix last 4 ingredients.
Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a buttered cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with cup crushed cornflakes. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook
noodles
(follow	directions on package).
Drain. Place in	lightly
greased casserole dish.
Top with drained, flaked tuna.
Melt
cheese
in
milk; add onion flakes.
Pour over tuna and noodles.
Bake approximately 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.	Serves 4.

title: souperior meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
In 9 X 13- inch baking or roasting pan, shape mixture into loaf.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour or until done.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: super duper biscuits
directions: Mix sifted flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry cutter until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Add milk and stir until blended.
Knead lightly on floured surface, about 10 times.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick, cut with a floured biscuit cutter.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet in a 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 12.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions. Drain and set aside.
Mix celery, onion, cheese and mayonnaise and then add cooked and drained vegetables.
Mix together well.
Top with crumbs and drizzle with melted margarine. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add boiling water gradually while stirring constantly. Boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add butter, lemon juice, salt and nutmeg.
Serve on steamed pudding.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix softened gelatin in cold water, then add white sugar.
Mix well.
Add the pineapple with juice.
Let chill until slightly thickened.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package.
Fold into the mixture.
Set aside.
Slice the angel food cake in 1/2-inch dices and then mix all the mixture and cake.
Let stand overnight.

title: crab and cream cheese cocktail
directions: Blend together first 6 ingredients.
Shape to fit in center of soup dish with rim or on a plate.
Cover with plastic.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: wacky cake
directions: In 8 x 8-inch pan/dish; do not grease pan and mix all dry ingredients.
Make 3 holes in mixture and put vinegar in 1; vanilla in second hole; and oil in third hole.
Pour cold water over all and mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Can easily be doubled and use 13 x 9-inch cake pan and adjust time for baking to 30 to 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick and when inserted toothpick comes out clean, it is done.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as package says.
Add apricot nector.
Put in large punch bowl.
Fill bowl with 7-Up.
Very good.

title: banana apricot shake
directions: Put ingredients in blender container. Blend until smooth. Makes 2 generous servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put potatoes and pineapple in 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cook and stir 12 marshmallows, sugar and butter until marshmallows melt.
Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 40 minutes.
Top with remaining marshmallows.
Return to oven for 3 to 4 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bean casserole
directions: Into a buttered 2-quart baking dish, place green beans, peas and lima beans.
Grate egg over this.
Combine mayonnaise, dressing and Worcestershire sauce; pour over vegetables.
Cover with onion rings.
Do not overbake as this causes casserole to water.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel-coconut pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and condensed milk with mixer (medium speed). Put 1/4 mixture in each crust. Drizzle caramel topping on mixture in crust (amount depends on personal
taste). Put rest of mixture in each crust. Sprinkle the toasted coconut and pecans on top (again amount depends on personal taste). Freeze.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream the softened cream cheese and marshmallow cream together.
Add vanilla.
Stir in confectioners sugar until desired dipping consistency.
A drop of food coloring may be added to match any color scheme.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo until it spins a thread when spoon is lifted out of syrup.
Pour syrup over egg whites slowly.
Add enough powdered sugar to make soft dough.
Turn out on board lightly dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread peanut butter and roll up jelly roll style. Slice in 1/2-inch slices.

title: apple-cranberry bake
directions: Mix apples, nuts and cranberries.
Stir flour over these.
Mix sugars, oatmeal and spices.
Add to first mixture.
Pour melted butter over all and mix well.
Pour in greased baking pan and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry and break up sausage; drain well. Cut crust off bread and discard. Butter both sides of bread and cut in cubes. Spread bread on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole. Top with sausage. Cover completely with grated cheese. Mix remaining ingredients together; beat well. Pour liquid over top of cheese, sausage and bread. At this point, you can refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until slightly brown. Good with buttered muffins.

title: apple and pepper relish
directions: Grind all together.
Boil sugar and vinegar.
Pour over relish.
Put on stove.
Get it hot and put into sterilized jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple brownies
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients, except pineapple, chocolate and walnuts (optional).
Blend well with mixer.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine sour cream and taco mix.
Mix thoroughly.
In a large glass baking dish, layer ingredients in order given in ingredients.

title: mushroom croustades
directions: Brush 24 tiny muffin tins heavily with butter.
Cut out rounds of bread with 3-inch fluted or plain cutter and press gently into cups.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° until golden brown.
Remove from tins and cool.
These freeze well.

title: chicken fettucini
directions: Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add milk and cheese.
Heat on low until cheese is melted. Fold in noodles and chicken. Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and soda; blend well.
Stir in shortening; add sour cream, corn and eggs, mixing well.
Spoon half of batter into a greased skillet.
Sprinkle with cheese and chilies; cover with remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake at 375 ° for 35 or 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: clam fritters
directions: Drain clams and chop fine.
Combine flour and baking powder. Beat eggs; add milk or clam juice and add slowly to flour.
Mix well, then add clams.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drop from a spoon into hot fat.
Fry at 375° until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: confetti bread
directions: Cut French bread in half lengthwise.
Mix ingredients and spread evenly on each half.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix puddings and jello with warm water.
Bring to a boil. Cook 2 or 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool completely.
Fold in mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Scald milk and add butter, sugar and salt.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add mashed potatoes and mix well. Cool to lukewarm.
Add the yeast and half of the flour.
Mix well. Beat in eggs.
Add remaining flour and mix thoroughly.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Layer in casserole in order listed.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: jimmy dean easter casserole
directions: Brown the sausage, onions and pepper; drain.
Line a baking dish with 3/4 of the sausage mixture.
Combine eggs and sour cream.
Season to taste.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° until the eggs are semi-set.
Stir egg mixture and top with remaining sausage.
Bake until the eggs are firm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dilled peas
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except peas) and chill overnight.
Add peas several hours before serving.
Before serving, sprinkle top with six slices of crisp bacon (crumbled) and 4 ounce package of cashews (unsalted or salted and chopped).

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl combine eggs and milk; stir in bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, sage and pepper.
Add ground meat. Thoroughly mix meat and seasonings.
Spoon meat mixture into 5 1/2 cup ring mold or a loaf pan.
Firmly pat meat into mold.
Unmold mixture in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Spoon off the drippings and fat.

title: jan's party mix
directions: Toss in a large bowl; exact amounts specified are not necessary.
Mix it as you like it.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: cheesy hamburger helper
directions: Mix according to package directions. Add cheese on top. Allow to melt.

title: palm's swedish sugar cookies
directions: Mix together, margarine, oil, sugars, eggs, and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and add to other ingredients. Refrigerate for 2 hours or more. Roll in small balls, the size of a walnut. Flatten with a glass that is dipped in water then sugar. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mealtime minestrone
directions: Combine turkey thighs, carrots, celery, potatoes, onions, basil, oregano, bouillon cubes, kidney beans, garlic, tomatoes and water in 10-quart pan.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry apple pie*
directions: Mix sugar, flour, allspice, salt, lemon rind and honey in a saucepan and heat to blend mixture.
Add cranberries and apples and let cool.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Line strips of crust for lattice top.
Brush top with milk and bake in hot oven (425°) for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and apples are tender.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together with a fork.
Great to dip apples in.

title: chocolate cream dessert
directions: In a bowl, cut butter into cake mix until crumbly.
Add egg and mix with electric mixer.
Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 in. baking dish.
Bake at 350°F for 15 - 18 min. or until set.
Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar until smooth.
Fold in 1 c. of whipped topping.
Carefully spread over the crust, refrigerate.
Whisk milk and pudding for 2 min.; let stand until slightly thickened.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Top with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate 2 hours before eating.
(12 servings.)

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 400°.
Turn out onto baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes longer, or microwave on High in round tube pan for 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add wet ingredients.
Let set for a while and roll out as needed.
Leftovers can be frozen until needed.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine and beat sweet potatoes, 2 cups sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla, coconut and salt.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Cook until glossy.
Combine pineapple, cherries and juice, 2 cups sugar and cornstarch; pour over potatoes.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Mix soups and milk.
Place chicken in baking dish; pour soups on top.
Mix the stuffing mix, margarine and chicken broth together; put on top of soups.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chili
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil. Brown beef and add beans, tomato sauce, tomatoes and vinegar. Mix well and let start cooking, then add chili powder, red pepper, salt and oregano. Cook for 3 hours, then mix cornmeal and water together and pour into mixture, stirring well. Let cook 15 minutes longer.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then add last 4 ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Ice with your favorite icing.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine flour with sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla and mix until well blended.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30-35 minutes until custard is set.

title: peanut fingers
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together; stir in.
Chill about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Put through cookie press, making 2 1/2-inch length cookie.
Use star shape plate.
Bake on greased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake from 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned. When cool, dip one end in melted chocolate and then in crushed peanuts.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a small bowl, combine ingredients.
Beat at low speed to mix, then at high speed to blend smoothly.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Heat drippings; blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Gradually blend in broth and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Combine potatoes and bacon bits.
Pour sauce over; toss gently and put in serving dish.
Put in oven at 325 degrees to reheat for 1/2 hour.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Turn in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: herb butter roasted chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Secure wings to body of chicken.
In small bowl, stir remaining ingredients.
Rub chicken with butter mixture.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fat free lasagna
directions: Brown and drain meat, onion and pepper.
Mix in sauce.
Put a layer of sauce into two 9 x 13-inch pans; followed with a layer of noodles, Mozzarella and Cheddar.
Sprinkle with some Parmesan and repeat, starting with sauce, until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fiesta brunch casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray both halves of tortillas with cooking spray.
Place 2 tortillas into each of 2 loaf pans, gently shaping each into a "bowl".
In a medium saucepan heat chili. Stir in potatoes; cook until thoroughly heated.
Divide chili mixture among tortillas.
With back of spoon make an indentation in each chili mixture.
Break egg into each indentation.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until eggs are done.
Gently lift out of pans to serving plates. Spoon on tomato and onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with salsa (optional).

title: orange pecans
directions: Cook water, sugar and corn syrup together until it spins a thread.
Remove from heat and add salt, orange juice and grated rind.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and beat until nuts separate with candy on them.
Pour onto buttered platter.

title: prune torte
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add flour, baking powder, salt and eggs.
Beat well. Spoon into 9 inch spring-form pan.
Arrange prunes, skin side up.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: blue cheese chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter with garlic until white.
Place in baking dish.
In same skillet, brown
mushrooms and melt Bleu cheese.
Turn heat off and add sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: curried zucchini soup
directions: Cook onion and apple in butter until soft. Add curry and stir 4 to 5 seconds. Add chicken stock; bring to a boil. Add rice, diced zucchini and salt; cook until soft. Put through a food processor and then add milk.
Serve hot or cold with croutons or slivered almonds.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour cold water in bowl and sprinkle gelatin on top.
Add sugar, salt and hot water.
Stir until all is dissolved.
Add lemon and mix thoroughly.
Put into fridge.
Allow to jell somewhat.
Cut fruit into small pieces.
Drain cherries and pineapple and cut.
Add fruit to jello when it is thickened somewhat.
Oil mold and rinse in cold water.
Pour mixture into mold and refrigerate.
To remove from mold, dip into hot water.

title: too-easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with a nonstick coating.
Cut crust from bread, then cut each slice of bread into five fingers.
Place the bread fingers over the peaches.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and butter.
Pour over fruit and bread.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: better-for-you pound cake
directions: Place cake mix, buttermilk, applesauce, egg whites and flour in bowl.
Blend with mixer on low for 1 minute.
Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes more.
Pour into a 12-cup bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
Cool. Invert cake onto a serving platter.
Poke hoes in top and sides of cake.
Brush cake generously all over with the sweetened condensed milk.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Lightly cover with plastic wrap and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: lazy pierogi(microwave)
directions: Cook bows as directed on package; drain.
Saute onion in oleo. In greased dish, layer bows, potatoes, cheese and onion mixture. Heat in microwave until cheese melts.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Cut avocado in half.
Scoop out pulp.
Mash pulp thoroughly. Blend in 1/2 tablespoon lemon juice, salt, chili pepper and onion. At this point if dip is to be used at a later hour, spread mayonnaise over avocado mixture.
When ready to serve, mix mayonnaise into avocado mix and serve.

title: uncle jim's jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over high heat.
Add sausage and ham; cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add chicken and continue cooking until chicken is brown, approximately 4 or 5 more minutes.
Stir frequently.
Stir in bay leaves, Poultry Magic and 1/2 cup each of onion, celery and green pepper.
Add garlic.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes, until vegetables start to soften.
Stir in tomato sauce and cook about 1 minute.
Remember to stir often and scrape bottom of pan well.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Chop zucchini, red and green peppers and onions; drain off excess liquid.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until tender, about 45 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Makes about 12 pints.

title: strawberry bavarian crown angel cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin/Jell-O in hot water.
Add ice water and chill until slightly candied.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Drain berries and reserve juice for "Ruby Glaze".
Fold in the strawberries and whipped cream.
With forks, tear angel food cake into small pieces.
Alternate cake pieces and gelatin mixture into a 10-inch angel food cake pan.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Make the "Ruby Glaze" and let drip down sides. Chill and serve.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Warm pecans for 10 minutes in oven. Melt butter; set aside.
Beat eggs and gradually add sugar until stiff.
Stir pecans and meringue together.
Stir meringue-nut mixture into melted butter.
Spread out on a cookie sheet; bake for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes, or until butter is absorbed.
Cool.
Great gift idea or appetizer.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put cubed bread in buttered 9 x 14-inch baking pan.
Layer with cooked and drained sausage.
Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients to the eggs.
Pour over the bread and sausage. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: baked herbed potatoes
directions: Mix cheese, basil and pepper.
Halve the potatoes longways. Brush cut surfaces with lemon-butter mix.
Dip in cheese mixture. Place coated side down in a spoke pattern on a glass pie plate. Microwave on High 14 to 16 minutes until potatoes are tender and edges lightly browned.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, soda and baking powder.
Add oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: red applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve cinnamon candies in the hot water before adding to jello and applesauce.
Serves 8.

title: nut butter balls
directions: Mix together the butter and sugar until fluffy, then add the salt, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill until it is easy handle.

title: spicey breast of chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 13x9x2 inch baking dish. Pour margarine and lime or lemon juice over chicken; sprinkle with salad dressing mix. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until tender. Yield 8 servings.

title: chilled tomato salad
directions: Drain tomatoes; cut into chunks.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in a little water until tender.
Cook carrots and onions in skillet in small amount of margarine until tender. Stir in stuffing crumbs and add soup or sour cream.
Fold in drained zucchini.
Put in casserole.
May top with more croutons. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix the filling.
Place a small amount of filling in an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Warm each tortilla, fill, roll up and place in pan. Cover the enchiladas with the remaining filling.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hearty fluffy whole wheat waffles
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients together in 2-quart bowl.
In separate container add vanilla to milk; stir.
Add liquid ingredients to dry and stir.
Add butter or margarine and egg yolks and stir.
Batter should be lumpy but consistent.
Fold whipped egg whites into batter.
Pour into waffle iron and cook until golden brown to brown.
Yields 7 seven-inch round waffles.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Clean and cut up chicken.
Put oil or Crisco in pan and brown chicken.
After browning slightly, add soy sauce, vinegar and water.
Shake in garlic salt and pour in vinegar.
Sprinkle paprika and onion over all.
Add bay leaf.
Cover.
Cook for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve with rice, green vegetable and salad.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually; beat until stiff.
Add Pet milk, milk, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes.
Dip into egg, then crumbs or flour, then carefully into egg and crumbs or flour again.
Melt butter or shortening in a large skillet.
Add green tomato slices and cook slowly until golden brown on each side and tomato is tender. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: supper club sausage tidbits
directions: Preheat gas oven to 375°.
Slice sausage links into 1-inch bite size pieces.
Combine chili sauce, brown sugar and bourbon in oven-proof casserole dish.
Add sausage links and stir well. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Chill overnight.
To serve, reheat at 375° until hot.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place butter in casserole dish in oven to melt.
Then let cool before adding batter of flour, sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over butter.
Drain 1 cup juice off peaches.
Pour remaining juice and peaches into center of mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: meringue for pie
directions: Combine water, cornstarch and 2 tablespoons sugar; mix well. Cook until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Add remaining sugar and beat stiff.
Add cold custard mixture; fold in well.
Spread on pie.
Bake at 350° to brown.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix together.
Add chips and dressing just before serving.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Pour hot water over nuts and raisins & let set. Mix flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, cocoa, salt. Add water mixture and mix well. Then add one cup mayonnaise and vanilla and mix well.
Bake 350° till done.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Food processor or Salad Shooter works nicely to chop into small pieces.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Add raisins, nuts, dates and chocolate chips to suit you. Blend shortening, sugar, eggs and raisins, dates, nuts, chocolate chips and pineapple.
Alternate adding flour and oatmeal.
Put soda in milk and add to mixture.
Cinnamon and salt go in flour.

title: microwave flounder
directions: Prepare sauce of choice (cocktail or cucumber).
On wax paper combine corn flakes, parsley, lemon peel and paprika.
Dip fillets in egg, then coat with crumb mixture.
On rack set shallow baking dish; cook on High 5 to 6 minutes, until edges of fish flake, then arrange on lettuce.
Serve with sauce of choice.
Garnish with radishes and cucumber slices.
