title: chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken with red pepper and sage in enough water to cover the chicken.
Let cool.
Pick chicken off the bones, making sure all skin, fat, gristle and cartilage are removed.
Break chicken into bite size pieces.
Put back into broth and bring to a slow bowl.
Mix in the pint of milk while stirring.
Thorough mix the remaining cup of milk and flour.
Add to broth after it begins to boil, stirring vigorously several times.
During the cooking and stirring, skim the small pieces of fat, skin, etc., which come to the top.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat until well mixed.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Stir in flour; blend in nuts.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: zippy mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions and mushrooms. Mix well; add onions and mushrooms. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: molded waldorf salad
directions: In medium bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
In separate bowl, slowly stir cold water and lemon juice into mayonnaise and sour cream.
Combine mayonnaise mixture with gelatin mixture in bowl.
Chill apples, celery and walnuts.

title: crab imperial
directions: Combine crab meat, egg, salt and pepper.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco in separate bowl.
Fold crab meat mixture in mayonnaise mixture.
Pack in individual shells or casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Place butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: wild horse barbecued beans
directions: Fry salt pork over medium heat.
When it is rendered but not yet crisp, add onion and cook until onion is soft.
Drain canned beans of excess liquid and combine them with salt pork, drippings and onion.
Stir in molasses, brown sugar, mustard, ginger, cayenne pepper, cumin, jalapeno pepper and barbecue sauce.
Pour into earthenware pot or casserole.
Stir in extra chunks of already barbecued meat, if desired.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gnocchi, parisian-style
directions: Cook gnocchi according to package directions.
Set aside.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine drained crushed pineapple and mini marshmallows. Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
In a small saucepan mix sugar, vinegar, egg, flour and juice from pineapple.
Cook until creamy and thick.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
After several hours or the next day, combine the ingredients with the red apples, peanuts and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: endive dressing
directions: Cut and clean endive; cut in bite-size pieces.
Put in bowl with diced onion.
Cut bacon in small pieces and fry until crisp. Drain on paper towels.
Blend together sugar, vinegar, 2 cups water, salt and pepper in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Once boiling, add cornstarch mixed with 1/4 cup water; stir until thickened.
Makes a nice, creamy dressing.
Pour dressing over endive.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Place the unpeeled potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with water; cook until tender, but firm.
Drain; cut potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Place in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: new potatoes with dill
directions: Wash potatoes; cut into 3/8-inch thick slices.
In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, arrange potatoes in a thin layer.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with dill and salt.
Cover and bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until tender, stirring after 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti soup
directions: In a 5 or 6-quart Dutch oven, brown ground beef and drain. Stir in water, juice, salt, seasoning, pepper, onion, tomatoes and cabbage.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Prepare spaghetti according to package directions and drain.
Add frozen vegetables and cooked spaghetti into soup mixture; heat thoroughly.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 quarts.

title: fruit float
directions: Fill a tall glass with your favorite fruit.
Pour in chilled ginger ale.
Top with 1 scoop of lime sherbet or any other kind of sherbet you like.

title: pineapple bread(yields 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Mix sugar and butter, creamed together.
Add egg and mix dry ingredients.
Mix in cherries, nuts and pineapple.
Make in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan, floured and greased.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or plain.
May be made ahead of time and put in freezer.

title: baked manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cheeses, eggs and seasonings. Mix well.
Pour 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Fill manicotti shells with 3 tablespoons cheese mixture and arrange sauce over top and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese. Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: frozen fruit salad(make ahead recipe)
directions: Mix together sour cream, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Blend in pineapple, walnuts and cherries.
Mix in banana.
Line 10 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan wells with paper baking cups.
Spoon mixture into cups and freeze until firm.
Remove papers before serving on lettuce.
Let stand at room temperature for a short while to soften slightly or pour entire mixture into mold and freeze (the night before at least).

title: cornbread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together and set aside.
Mix the milk and eggs together and add to the dry ingredients.
Add the melted butter and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday sparkle punch
directions: Blend juices in punch bowl.
Add ice to chill.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces almond bark in 2-quart dish for 2 minutes on High; stir.
Continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes until smooth when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour into greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: sand tarts
directions: To butter, add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add the flour and baking powder.
Add pecans and mix well.
Roll out into ropes.
Cut about 2 inch lengths and shape into crescents as you place onto a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° 10-12 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: quick dried beans
directions: Drain the beans in a colander. Rinse beans with cool water. Place beans in Dutch oven or large saucepan. Cover with water. Add flavorings, spices, seasonings, etc.
Bring to a boil and cook for 30 minutes. Serve with cornbread.

title: hot biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut or rub shortening into flour mixture until particles are as fine as coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir in with a fork.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead just until smooth.
Roll dough out to about 1/2 inch thickness and cut with a floured cutter.
Place biscuits on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 o 12 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.

title: anna's carrot layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice.
Dissolve lime gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in 2 cups cold water.
Pour into a 9x13 pan.
Chill until partially set.

title: bret's dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Place back in pan and add taco mix. In crock-pot, add cheese `n' salsa dip and Pace chunky salsa; heat on high. Add hamburger to crock-pot and heat for a while. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: four-fruit compote
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup juice.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat; set aside.

title: canned okra
directions: Add vinegar and salt to okra.
Cover okra with water; bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Put in hot jars.
Add liquid to cover okra.
Seal with hot lids.
To cook:
Rinse well.
Add to soups, etc. or rinse well and add small amount of corn meal.
Shake well. Fry in small amount of olive oil or other oil.
Oil should be hot. Makes 9 or 10 pints.

title: tijuana casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with diced onion. Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, chiles, taco seasoning, olives, corn and picante sauce.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer 1/2 sauce, noodles and sour cream.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: turkey chili(heart healthy cooking)
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in margarine in Dutch oven.
Add turkey and cook until it loses pink color.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except beans. Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer one hour.
Stir in beans, cover and simmer an additional 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, chilies, soup and cheese together.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with French fried onions. Place in a 375° oven and bake until bubbly and brown.

title: beef stroganoff casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is light brown and drain.
Stir in noodles, sauce mix, water, sour cream and mushrooms (with liquid). Heat to boiling and pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: katherine's gravy for dressing
directions: Your broth should contain the celery and onions from the cooking of the chicken or turkey.
If not, add seasonings to taste. Stir flour in 3/4 cup of water.
Let broth come to boil; stir flour into broth.
Stir continuously until smooth with a wire whip or stirrer.
Put a couple of drops of yellow food coloring in.
Chop the gizzards and boiled eggs; add to the gravy.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray a 8 x 8 inch baking dish and place cubed bread in bottom. Spread cooked and drained sausage over bread. Stir together salt and ground mustard to blend, then add eggs and milk, beating well.
Add cheese, pour over bread and sausage. Bake about 40 minutes at 350° until center is cooked.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Arrange in casserole 4 times:
1/4 cabbage, 1/4 cream of mushroom soup, 1/4 bacon and grease and 1/4 cheese.
Let set all day or overnight.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil whole soup chicken slow for 1 hour.
Then remove to a bowl to cool.
Add vegetables and boil for 1/2 hour with spices.
Add frozen spinach the last 10 minutes, if desired.
After chicken has cooled, clean away from bone and add back to the pot.

title: nut cracker
directions: Mix cheese, pineapple and pecans.
Spread on crackers.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown rice and onion in 3 tablespoons of margarine.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: southern style scalloped corn
directions: Combine all.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: dessert brownies
directions: Bake brownies as instructed on box.
As soon as you remove from oven, put marshmallows on top; cover for 10 minutes with foil.
Take foil off and spread marshmallows evenly over brownies. Let cool completely, then ice.
Decorate with pecan halves or cherries.

title: party shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Scoop out center portion of bread, leaving crust intact.
Tear removed portion into bite sized pieces; set aside.
Pour dip into cavity of bread.
Garnish with parsley sprigs and cherry tomatoes.
Serve with reserved pieces of bread.
Also good with Wheat Thins.

title: hamburger medley
directions: Mix half of pepper in meat and brown in nonstick skillet. Remove hamburger from skillet and put in colander and run it under hot water to rinse off extra fat.
In skillet, brown onions, green peppers, mushrooms and garlic.
Put brown hamburger on top of onion mixture in skillet.
Add tomatoes and remaining pepper.
Top with noodles which have been scalded with boiling water.
Cover and cook 30 minutes or until noodles are done.
Turn off heat and allow to stand, covered, 5 to 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: serbian eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Melt 1-inch cube of butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour ingredients into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Serves 6 to 10 people.
Perfect for brunch or supper!

title: seven layer squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put the margarine and melt in the preheating oven.
When melted, add the graham cracker crumbs and press in the pan.
Sprinkle on top the coconut, chocolate and butterscotch chips and nuts.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk over all.
Bake 25 to 28 minutes until golden brown.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to package directions.
Saute onion in butter.
Add soup and milk to onion.
Heat until smooth. Drain broccoli and add to mixture.
Drain rice and add to mixture. Cut cheese up into mixture and stir until melted.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: candy cane punch
directions: Put all ingredients except candy canes and ginger ale into blender container.
Cover and process until candies are liquified. Divide evenly between four tall glasses.
Fill with ginger ale. Stir gently.
Serve with peppermint candy canes as stirrers.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In an 8 x 12-inch dish or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, smooth the pie filling.
Add the pineapple and juice over cherries.
Sprinkle sugar over pineapple.
Smooth dry cake mix over sugar.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix and spread the first 3 ingredients in bottom of sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar; put on top of pretzel layer and refrigerate.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Wash chicken parts thoroughly; drain.
Combine other ingredients in large bowl.
Place chicken in bowl; let sit for at least 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator.
Spread oil in casserole dish; place chicken in dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° to 375°, until done.

title: sandy's polish sausage and cabbage
directions: Put cabbage and water in large pot.
Add salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Add sausage wheels; simmer.
Add carrots. Scrub or peel potatoes; cut in chunks and add to simmering pot. Cover tightly; cook for 35 minutes after adding potatoes.
Serve. A good, one-pot dish for 4!

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut bread lengthwise into 2 pieces; spread mushroom soup on bread with knife.
Roll each one inside 1/2 piece of bacon and secure with toothpick.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done.
(You can also use the broiler.)

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti in 2-inch lengths and cook in salted water until tender.
Cut chicken into small pieces and mix with drained spaghetti.
Add remaining ingredients reserving 1 cup of cheese. Spread the 1 cup of cheese over the entire mixture and bake about 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: thousand island pickles
directions: Boil cucumbers and onions until tender.
Drain.
Then add vinegar, sugar, flour, salt, celery seed and turmeric.
Mix all together.
Boil 5 minutes.
Jar and seal.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: In bowl mix, Crisco and boiling water with fork until Crisco is thoroughly mixed.
Add salt and flour.
Work dough into a ball. Roll out dough for your pie.

title: hero burger
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread evenly on 1 medium loaf (split like a sandwich) French bread or use sub rolls.
Cover edges completely otherwise they tend to burn.
Broil about 4 inches from heat about 12 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: fried apples
directions: Heat grease in skillet.
Add apples, sugar and water.
Cover and fry over low heat until tender.

title: snack for cocktails
directions: Combine the ingredients (not bread).
Cut crusts from bread slices.
Flatten them by rolling each slice with a rolling pin. Spread with cheese mixture and roll each slice from corner to corner and secure with a toothpick.
Bake in a 400° oven on baking sheet until cheese is melted and rolls are brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Um m m m.

title: crabmeat muffins
directions: Take the stick of butter and 2 jars of cheese and place in a microwavable pan.
Melt the butter and cheese.
Take an egg beater (whisk) and beat until smooth.
Add a dash of garlic powder (if you like a real garlic taste, you can add fresh garlic); add crabmeat and mix well.
Spread on English muffins.
Put on cookie sheets and refrigerate for at least 45 minutes.
Preheat oven for 15 minutes or until light brown around the edges.
I then turn my oven on broil and cook a few minutes.
Eat and enjoy!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well; store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Beat eggs first; add sugar, then other ingredients.
Mix well. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: irish cream
directions: Put all of the ingredients except the cream in a blender and mix well.
Add the heavy cream slowly and blend well.
Put in a bottle with a tight top and refrigerate.
Shake well before serving.

title: holiday twistys
directions: Combine flour, yeast and baking soda; set aside.
Heat milk, shortening, sugar and salt until warm, stirring constantly.
Add dry ingredients.
Add egg. Beat at low 1/2 minute.
Scrape bowl and beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 flour, enough to make dough moderately stiff.
Turn on to floured board. Knead 5 times.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Halve dough.
Roll out 14 x 6-inch rectangle.
Spread 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle 2 tablespoons red sugar crystals on dough.
Fold in half long ways.
Cut into 14 (1-inch) strips.
Twist.
Put on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Make up other half of dough with green sugar crystals.
Ice with powdered sugar icing after they are cooled.

title: bacon & jalapeno dip
directions: Mix cream cheese.
Fry bacon until crisp.
When cool crumble and add to cream cheese.
Chop Jalapeno fine then add to cream cheese and bacon.
Serve with nachos.

title: barbecued chicken(conk)
directions: Cut chicken in half.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in pan with enough hot water to just cover bottom of the pan.

Slice one large onion for each chicken and put under the wings and legs. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°; turn and bake for 30 minutes more. Then pour about three-quarters of the sauce over the chicken and bake for 1 hour longer, skin sides up.
Pour the remaining sauce over the chicken just before serving.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, buttermilk and butter; slowly stir into dry ingredients. Batter will be very thick.
For each pancake, spoon about 1/4 cup batter onto a hot, lightly greased griddle.
Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges are brown.

title: arlie's chili
directions: Brown meat and drain grease, then add onion and beans.
In a bowl, make paste with chili powder, salt, flour and enough water to make a thin paste.
Put paste and ketchup in meat and add 1/2 cup water.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: low sugar punch
directions: Add 2 quarts of diet 7-Up before serving.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Soak tortillas in chicken broth and place in bottom of 3-quart casserole. Saut green peppers and onions in oil until tender. Put over chicken. Add 3/4 cheese; sprinkle with chili powder, garlic and salt. Spoon undiluted soups over and top with crushed tomatoes and chilies. Add rest of cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Mix brown sugar, water and 2 tablespoons butter.
Bring to a boil.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, butter, milk and cinnamon together.
Put this mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour first mixture on top.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipping cream.

title: breakfast crumb cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, salt and cream of tartar. Blend in oleo. Work as for pie dough.
Take out 3/4 cup crumbs for topping.
Add eggs (beaten slightly) and 1 cup buttermilk alternately to first mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Dissolve baking soda in 1/4 cup buttermilk and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Divide batter into three 7-inch pie pans, greased and floured.
Top with crumbs.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake
at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: minnesota cake frosting
directions: This is an easy recipe to make and it tastes like whipped cream!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients and roll in pecans.
Keep in refrigerator until time to serve.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: lasagne
directions: Over medium heat, saute onion in 2 tablespoons oil until onion is tender.
Add ground beef; cook until meat is brown.
Add the chili powder, Tabasco sauce and salt.
Simmer over low heat for a few minutes.
Taste; if not hot enough, add more chili powder and Tabasco sauce.
Add tomato sauce, tomato soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Stir often; sauce is bad to stick.
Cook noodles.
Alternate noodles, meat and cheese in a baking pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Allow to drain well.
Brown ground beef and season to taste with oregano and black pepper.
Drain in colander to get all grease out.
In a large bowl, combine spaghetti, beef and all vegetables.
Sprinkle Salad Supreme over this mixture and add dressing last, tossing to cover all ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors.
Makes 8 servings.

title: red and green cabbage slaw
directions: Combine vegetables and cheese in bowl.	Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, Equal and celery seed; stir into cabbage mixture.	Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture onto lettuce lined plates, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and beat for four minutes. Pour into well greased and floured bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Turn onto plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers and remove seeds.
Boil peppers for 4 minutes in rapidly boiling water or in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Drain.

title: chicken tahitian
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, melt butter; stir in onion soup mix and cornstarch, then reserved pineapple juice and lime or lemon juice.
Arrange chicken and pineapple chunks in oblong baking dish; pour onion mixture over and bake 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 6 servings.
(I usually bake about 1 hour.)

title: can cake
directions: Wash the can syrup comes in and use this for your measuring cup.
Mix
syrup, eggs, sugar and shortening together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: taco bites
directions: For filling, in a small skillet, cook ground beef until brown. Drain off fat.
Stir in taco sauce, chili powder, onion powder and garlic powder.
Set aside.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pour sorghum molasses into skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Stir continuously.
Boil until molasses strings from spoon.
Stir in soda.
Pour over popcorn and stir together.
Use ice or butter to prevent popcorn from sticking to your hands.
Form popcorn into balls and wrap with wax paper.

title: pineapple christmas pie
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour in baked pie crust or graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: beef-up biscuit casserole
directions: In frying pan, brown ground beef, onions and green pepper. Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing dough.
Separate biscuits; pull apart into 2 layers. Press 10 biscuits, layer over bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese (reserve remaining cheese for topping), sour cream and egg.
Mix well.
Remove meat mixture from heat; stir in sour cream mixture and spoon over dough. Arrange remaining biscuits on top; sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine crumbs, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and fat.
Mix well. Add vanilla.
Turn in greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: brownies
directions: Mix eggs and butter; add cocoa and mix well.
Add sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: glass custard
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Gradually add next 3 ingredients. Cook slowly until mixture slightly thickens.
Beat egg white until stiff with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Fold into custard. Add nutmeg or cinnamon, if desired.
Pour into tall glasses. Drink or eat with iced teaspoon.

title: strawberry fantasy salad
directions: Mix sugar, jello and hot water. Stir until dissolved.
Cool, then add strawberries, pineapple and banana.
Chill until jelly-like.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into mold rinsed with cold water. Chill until firm.
Garnish with whole strawberries.

title: jimmy carter cake
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and 1 cup ground peanuts together like pie crust.
Then put into 13 x 9-inch greased pan and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place filling on bottom, spreading fruit.
Put crushed pineapple on next layer. Do not mix.
Put cake mix as next layer.
Put spats of margarine all across cake mix. Put a layer of walnuts next and top with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato-cranberry nutbread
directions: To cook sweet potato, boil in water to cover for 30 to 40 minutes or bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until tender. Cool, peel and mash.
In a large mixing bowl, combine mashed sweet potato, brown sugar, butter, eggs, orange rind and orange juice. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and mace.
Blend into sweet potato mixture.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.

title: quick and easy frosting
directions: Mix the milk with the pudding mix; when pudding thickens, add the Cool Whip and fold in.
Frost cake and refrigerate.

title: egg sandwiches
directions: Mix hard-boiled egg, finely chopped, with mayonnaise dressing and spread on buttered bread, preferably graham.
Chopped olives may be added to the egg mixture, if desired.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add and mix eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Add flour, salt, cocoa, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add zucchini (add last).
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: honey cornmeal biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch on flour dusted surface.
Cut 2-inch circles. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes (475° for high altitude).

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cook in Bundt pan, greased and floured.
Beat until well blended butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well each time.
Blend in vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together and blend into creamed mixture.
Pour or spoon into pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar if you like, but great without.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients in microwave.
Add popcorn and pecans to mixture.
Add M&M's after the mixture has cooled.
Put in angel food or Bundt pan.
Firmly press mixture into pan.
Mixture will harden and slide out of pan.
Freezes well.

title: paprika chicken
directions: In skillet, melt butter and cook chicken 5 minutes on each side or until browned.
Remove from skillet.
Spoon off fat.
If you are doubling or tripling the recipe, be sure and add more butter.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Empty pineapple into large mixing bowl; add coconut, marshmallows, cherries, juice and nuts.
Fold in sour cream, cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve over sliced angel food cake, pound cake or in parfait dish.
Top with whole cherries.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt butter in casserole, dip chicken in milk roll in flakes crumbs.
Arrange in casserole, skin side down.
Cover chicken with remaining ingredients bake 20 minutes at 400 turn and bake 20 minutes more.

title: heart smart carrot pineapple juice
directions: In blender at medium speed, blend carrots and water about 1 minute.
Strain; return liquid to blender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend at low speed until smooth.
Pour into 2 glasses.
Makes 2 servings.

title: jamaica oxtail stew
directions: Place beans and 1 cup of water in small saucepan; bring to a boil, cover and turn off heat.
Allow to sit 1 hour, then drain. Brown the oxtail well in lard or oil.
Place the oxtails in a 6-quart stove-top casserole.
Add the garlic, onion, tomato and enough water to just cover contents of pot.
Add allspice, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 3 1/2 hours, adding the beans after 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Remove lid last hour for a thicker sauce.
Season with salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Serve with white cooked rice.

title: okra pickles
directions: Pack okra in hot jars.
Add dill, salt, garlic and hot pepper. Heat vinegar and water to boiling.
Pour over okra; seal. Process
15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 1 pint.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in a small amount of salted water in saucepan for 5 minutes; drain.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Chop water chestnuts.
Add to cabbage; mix well.
Add soup; mix well. Spread salad dressing over mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and stuffing mix.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° until mixture is hot and bubbly.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: finley's cole slaw
directions: Grate the cabbage, cucumber, green pepper and carrot; mix well.
Add the vinegar, mayonnaise, sugar and caraway seed.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: crumb cake - breakfast cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and butter; reserve 1 cup of slightly packed mix for crumbs.
Beat the remaining ingredients until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 cakes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll in balls and press down with a fork on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown, approximately 15 minutes.

title: california salad
directions: Stir salt into sour cream.
Combine other ingredients.
Fold into sour cream and chill overnight.
This salad will keep nicely for several days.

title: chinese hot dish
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery.
Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: cream of garlic soup
directions: Roast garlic by removing root, sprinkling with olive oil and roasting at 475° until tender.
Steam potatoes, then process in a food processor.
In large pan saute leeks until tender.
Add potatoes and garlic, then gradually add stock to form correct consistancy.
Finish with heavy cream and heat through.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
This soup is very good as the potatoes add a lot of body and the garlic is not overpowering. Serves 100.

title: fiesta pork bake
directions: Coat a shallow 2-quart casserole with melted margarine. Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper; arrange in casserole.
Top with soup mix, green pepper and rice.
Combine catsup and Worcestershire sauce; spread over rice.
Gently pour in boiling water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 55 or 60 minutes, until done. (Additional 1/2 cup of water may be added if casserole becomes too dry.)
Remove from oven; top with cheese.
Cover and allow to stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: kluski z kupustapo polski(cabbage soup)
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onion and saute until transparent.
Add cabbage and saute 5 minutes.
Stir in caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles; drain.
Stir noodles into cabbage.
Add sour cream.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine zucchini, onion, oil, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, biscuit mix, eggs and garlic to taste.
Place in 11 x 7-inch or 9-inch square greased baking dish.
Top with sprinkling of Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: egg bake
directions: In blender, blend eggs, cottage cheese, flour and milk. Season with dill weed, salt and pepper.
Stir in the grated Jack cheese.
Add chilies if desired.
Melt butter in a 7 x 12-inch pan.
Stir half into egg batter, then pour batter into pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans in blender.
Stir them in last, then pour into pie shells and cook 50 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter and 10x sugar together well.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup of mixture into a graham cracker crust pie shell.
Mix vanilla pudding mix and milk well and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with the remaining peanut butter mixture.
Top with Cool Whip topping.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Recipe is for one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: spanish hamburger
directions: Mix altogether and bake in oven at 350°.
Stir several times. Makes 24 sandwiches.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream 1/3 cup sugar, 1 cup margarine and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla. Blend flour in.
Spread dough onto greased pan and set up the sides.
Combine softened cheese and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Add 1 egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour on top of pastry and combine 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Mix with apples.
Spoon apple mixture over cream cheese.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake for 25 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli tuna bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Blend soup and milk into a smooth sauce.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Drain noodles.
Layer 1 1/2 cups noodles, 1/3 cup tuna and 1 cup broccoli in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour in 1 cup of sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 20 minutes, then add cheese and bake 15 more minutes.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper.
Add soup, water and rice.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix cake
mix, butter and egg together and pat into 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Then
mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2	eggs.
Pour over crust mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: rocky road squares
directions: In top of double boiler over simmering water, melt chocolate. Remove from heat and stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Line 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with aluminum foil.
Spread chocolate mixture in baking dish; cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or until set.
Makes 16 servings.

title: ambrosia fruit dip
directions: Blend cheese and sour cream until smooth, then add other ingredients.
Mix and chill.
Makes 2 cups or 8 (1/2 cup) servings.
Four tablespoons per serving has 100 calories.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer in buttered 13 x 9-inch dish in following order: chicken, onion and chopped eggs.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken, onion and egg layers.

title: wild rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Drain mushrooms.
Add water to liquid to measure 2 3/4 cups.
Add to onion and boil.
Add wild rice and salt.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Add white rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until done.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: * beef with beans barbecue *
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and drain.
Add pork and beans, barbecue sauce, onion and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 lb. Velveeta cubes.
Pour into a baking dish.
Cut biscuits in half, forming half circles.
Place cut side down around edge of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with additional Velveeta slices.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Combine butter and sugar with a beater.
Add eggs. Add pineapple, nuts and whipped topping. Refrigerate. Cut apples into small pieces and add just before serving.

title: vivian's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, Wesson oil and spices.
Add pumpkin and flour.
Mix completely.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Mix celery soup,
milk	and
rice.
Pour
into 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Lightly salt and pepper chicken and place in mixture.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut into strips 4-inches long and 1/4-inch thick.
Put spices into bag.
Mix water, sugar, salt and spice. Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add carrots.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Carrots will be crisp.
Take out spice bag and store carrots in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days before serving.

title: simple herbed scallops for two
directions: In a small saucepan, melt 2 Tbsp. of butter. Add the lemon juice, chives, parsley, garlic salt, tarragon and pepper; stir well. Place scallops and mushrooms in a greased 1 quart baking dish. Pour butter mixture over scallops. Melt remaining butter and toss with bread crumbs; sprinkle over scallops. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until scallops are opaque and topping is lightly browned.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Boil water and butter; add flour and stir until pasty.
Add eggs and stir until smooth.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch glass pan (ungreased).
Bake at 400° until golden brown and puffy, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine corn and Jiffy mix well.
Pour half of batter into 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle peppers and half of cheese over batter.
Pour on remaining batter and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: tasty cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread on cookie sheet or large cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal cookies(allergy free)
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Blend in bananas.
Add oatmeal and raisins and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix altogether. Put in tow loaf pans, lined with wax paper. Layer topping with batter.

title: carrot cake 1
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add carrots, pineapple, and nuts; blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 14-inch pan or 3 (9-inch) round layer cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for layer pans, 40 to 50 minutes for 10 x 14-inch pan.
Cool 5 minutes in pan before turning out to cool thoroughly.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Layer chicken, broccoli, 1/2 of the sour cream and 1/2 of the soup.
Repeat layer.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fannie mae fudge
directions: Combine margarine, milk and sugars in large heavy saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil. Cover. Boil 5 minutes. Turn off heat and add marshmallows. Stir until dissolved. Add 3 kinds of chocolate, one at a time. Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into lightly greased 10 x 15 pan. Will keep for several months in refrigerator. Makes approximately 5 pounds.

title: claire's baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cut up tomatoes with juice in bowl and set aside.
Cook ziti for about 10 minutes and drain.
Using a casserole dish, start with tomato sauce and line bottom of the pan.
Next, layer with ziti, cheese slices, tomatoes and season layer with salt and pepper, then dot with margarine.
Continue layering and end with the tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes until cheese melts. Do not overcook.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and 2 cups sugar together.
Add orange juice, oil and vanilla; beat until light (about 5 minutes).
Add flour and baking powder, beat about 10 minutes.
Peel and slice apples.
Mix with 6 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Set aside.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased tube pan, then 1/2 of apple mixture.
Add rest of batter, then remaining apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: smoked sausage in rice creole
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch chunks; saute with onions and bell pepper.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid and catsup.
Blend and simmer 20 to 30 minutes; salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.
